<HEADLINE>
ATLANTA: 12th save.
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Devil Rays 5, Mets 4, 11 innings &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   In New York, Hideo Nomo pitched five inconclusive innings in his
debut with the Mets, who lost when Tampa Bay scored an unearned run
in the 11th.
	   Nomo's night was long over when John Hudek (0-3) walked the
first two in the 11th before retiring Bobby Smith on a foul bunt
with two strikes. After second baseman Luis Lopez's error loaded
the bases, Quinton McCracken hit a sacrifice fly to right
	   Jim Mecir (2-0) pitched 2 2-3 innings of relief for the win and
Roberto Hernandez got three outs for his 12th save.
 &UR; Rangers 5, Rockies 2 &QC; 
	   In Denver, Juan Gonzalez boosted his major league-leading RBI
total to 78 with a solo homer, and Will Clark also homered as Texas
handed Colorado its fifth straight loss.
	   Rick Helling (8-3) pitched six strong innings, allowing only one
run and four hits before tiring in the seventh. John Wetteland
pitched a perfect ninth for his 18th save.
	   The Rangers went ahead 4-1 with three runs, including Gonzalez's
20th homer, in the fourth off John Thomson (5-6).
	    &UR; MORE &QC; 
