<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Honduras-Evangelical Killings,0170 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Authorities say evangelical group used machetes to kill three
</HEADLINE>
attackers &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras (AP) _ About 60 people attending an
evangelical gathering used machetes to kill three men they believed
were planning to rob them and rape women, authorities said Tuesday.
A fourth man escaped.
	   Police said the four men disrupted the gathering Saturday night
in Calderas, a poor farming village of 300 people, about 120 miles
(200 kilometers) north of Tegucigalpa, the capital. The men fired
shots in the air and wounded the pastor's brother in the abdomen.
	   The men tried to flee after they ran out of ammunition, but the
crowd caught up with them and killed them with machete blows,
police said. The men were identified as Francisco Contreras, 26,
Benito Cruz, 24, and his brother Selvin, 28.
	   Police are looking for the fourth man, who was believed to have
escaped unharmed.
	   None of the evangelicals were arrested. Police say the
investigation is continuing.
</TEXT>
