<SLUG> BC-Pakistan-Rains,0122 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Cyclone storms across southern port city in Pakistan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) _ Rains battered Pakistan's southern port
city of Karachi, killing 12 people, as a cyclone plowed through the
area and into neighboring India, the state-run news agency said
Wednesday.
	   High winds and heavy rains lashed the city of 14 million people
throughout Tuesday, but most of the deaths, according to the
Associated Press of Pakistan, were the result of electrocution.
High winds toppled power lines, leaving live wires strewn across
several busy streets, the news agency said.
	   Several dwellings in Karachi's poorer neighborhoods also
collapsed, but police officials said there were only minor
injuries.
</TEXT>
