<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Russia-Trade Cuts </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russia to continue cuts in trade missions
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russia will continue a program of reducing the
size of its trade missions around the world with further cuts in
Africa, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported Tuesday.
	   The trade missions in South Africa, Mozambique and Nigeria will
be cut back and become departments of the Russian embassies in each
of those nations, the agency quoted government sources as saying.
	   Trade missions to some 40 nations have already been reduced as
part of the government's efforts to cut spending because of its
poor finances, the report said. In the past, Russian trade missions
were often separate entities with their own support staff and
facilities.
	   (ren)
</TEXT>
