<HEADLINE>
Sri Lanka wins toss and bats first in third Test against New
</HEADLINE>
Zealand &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) _ Sri Lanka won the toss Wednesday and
decided to bat first in the decisive third test against New Zealand
in Colombo.
	   The Indian Ocean islanders retained the same side that won the
second test by an innings, squaring the 3-match series 1-1.
	   New Zealand brought in left-arm spinner Mark Priest to replace
paceman Shyane O'Conner, while also leaving out allrounder Chris
Harris in favor of batsman Craig Spearman.
	   The match started an hour late due to rain.
	   Sri Lanka: Arjuna Ranatunga (capt.), Sanath Jayasuriya, Marvan
Atapattu, Mahela Jayawardena, Aravinda de Silva, Hashan
Tillekeratne, Romesh Kaluwitharana, Kumar Dharmasena, Pramodya
Wickremasinghe, Niroshan Bandaratilleke, Muttiah Muralitharan.
	   New Zealand: Stephen Fleming (capt.), Bryan Young, Mathew Horne,
Nathan Astle, Craig McMillan, Craig Spearman, Adam Parore, Chris
Cairns, Mark Priest, Daniel Vettori, Paul Wiseman.
	   Umpires: Peter Manuel (Sri Lanka), B.K. Ramaswamy (India).
	   Third umpire: Ranjan Anandappa (Sri Lanka).
