<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Bank Robbery </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Cashier siphons off bank's money, flees
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ A cashier diverted 12.5 million
ringgit (dlrs 3 million) secretly to his own account over two weeks
and fled overseas with part of the loot, a newspaper reported
Wednesday.
	   The employee of Bank Bumiputra Malaysia's branch in the southern
city of Johor disappeared, either to Hong Kong or mainland China,
with 5 million ringgit (dlrs 1.3 million), the New Straits Times
said.
	   The bank discovered the theft when it ordered an audit after the
cashier failed to return from a vacation. He had stashed away the
money in April in a secret fixed deposit account before leaving.
	   While the local police have sought help from Interpol to trace
the 43-year-old cashier, the bank has suspended two managers of the
Johor branch pending the results of an internal inquiry, the daily
said. 	   
</TEXT>
