	   SAN DIEGO _ Large balls of gas _ failed stars that glow faintly
like dying embers _ are a new class of stellar objects and may be
the most common bodies in the Milky Way, astronomers say. US-NEW
HEAVENLY BODY. Expected by 0700 GMT. By Paul Recer.
