<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-RugbyU-Scotland, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Lee and Metcalfe make Scotland team
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) _ New Zealanders Glenn Metcalfe and
Gordon Simpson will play their first tests for Scotland in
Saturday's opening match of a two-game series against Australia.
	   Metcalfe and Simpson qualify because of Scottish grandparents.
	   ``Both are very professional and have been brought up in a good
rugby culture,'' said Scotland coach Jim Telfer. ``They've brought
something positive to the game.''
	   Scotland's selectors have chosen both fullbacks, Metcalfe and
Derrick Lee, in the starting side. Lee, who played at fullback in
the 51-26 loss to Fiji at the start of the tour, has moved to the
wing.
	   There are five changes from the loss in Suva, but only one from
the side which scored an encouraging victory over a below-strength
New South Wales team last Saturday.
	   Lee replaces Craig Joiner from that team.
	   Scotland lost to an Australian Barbarians team Tuesday in the
final match before the first of two tests.
	   Coach Jim Telfer said he was happy with his team's form, while
Australia will be backing up after a record 76-0 win over England
on Saturday.
	   Australia named an unchanged lineup from the one which inflicted
England's worst-ever defeat and gave the Wallabies their
biggest-ever victory.
	   Lee scored two tries in Tuesday's match to force his way back
into contention after it appeared he had lost his place.
	   ``Lee's attacking flair against the Australian Barbarians
impressed us,'' Telfer said.
	   Simpson made certain of the openside flanker position with
excellent displays against New South Wales Country and New South
Wales.
	   Rowen Shepherd is another fullback having to play out of his
usual position. He will start at inside center after turning around
a career which appeared to be flagging as Lee and Metcalfe went
past him in the fullback rankings.
	   Scotland:
	   Glenn Metcalfe, Derrick Lee, Cameron Murray, Rowen Shepherd,
Shaun Longstaff, Gregor Townsend, Bryan Redpath, Eric Peters,
Gordon Simpson, Robert Wainwright (captain), Stuart Grimes, Scott
Murray, Matthew Proudfoot, Gordon Bulloch, David Hilton. Reserves:
Craig Joiner, Duncan Hodge, Graeme Burns, Adam Roxburgh, Stewart
Campbell, Gordon McIlwham, Kevin McKenzie.
 &UR; (tjh)
</TEXT>
