<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Israel-Shooting </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Israel says Palestinian killed while planting bomb near settlement
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   GAZA CITY, Gaza Strip (AP) _ A Palestinian was shot and killed
Tuesday night by Israeli troops who surprised him and another man
as they were planting two bombs outside a settlement in the Gaza
Strip, the army said Wednesday.
	   The army had said earlier that the two men were trying to cut
through the security fence surrounding the settlement, but in a
search of the area the soldiers found two explosive charges with
electric detonation devices. The bombs were probably intended to be
used against an army patrol which was due to pass, the army said.
	   The soldiers ordered the men to halt, but they ran off and the
troops opened fire, killing Mohammed Bardawilbal, a resident of
Khan Yunis. The other man got away.
	   Palestinian police commander Khaled Abu Oleh said a joint
Israeli-Palestinian investigation into the incident was underway.
	   ``We are following in detail what happened and we cannot give
full information until we finish our investigation,'' Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat told reporters Wednesday morning.
	   Most of the Gaza Strip is under Palestinian control, while
Israel retains control of the areas around Jewish settlements and
the borders of the strip with Israel and Egypt.
 &UR; jk-hla
