<HEADLINE>
7 killed in German house fire
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BOCHUM, Germany (AP) _ Seven people were killed and five others
injured in an early morning house fire in the west German city of
Bochum Wednesday.
	   Police said the fire began in the top floor of the five-story,
turn-of-the-century building and quickly spread. Rescue efforts
were hampered by the danger the structure would collapse.
	   The five injured suffered light smoke inhalation. The fire's
cause was unknown, but arson was not suspected, police said.
