<SLUG> BC-Air France-Strike </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Air France reaches accord with striking pilots, says French radio
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Air France has reached an agreement with striking
pilots to end a ten-day walkout which has severely undermined
preparations for the World Cup, French radio reported Wednesday.
	   France Info said the agreement was reached Wednesday. No further
details were given.
	   The strike has caused acute embarrassment for Air France, the
World Cup's official carrier, and the French government.
	   The World Cup kicks off later Wednesday with a match between
Brazil and Scotland.
	   An estimated one million fans are expected to travel to France
for the month-long soccer tournament. Many fans have already
arrived. Many have been forced to switch airlines.
	   The pilots have been protesting a proposal for dlrs 500 million
francs of (83 million) in salary cuts.
	   (ip)
