<BODY>
<SLUG> BC_Japan-Earthquake </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mild quake shakes western Japan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ A mild earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of
4.3 shook Nara and its neighboring areas in western Japan
Wednesday, but there were no immediate reports of damage or
injuries.
	   The Central Meteorological agency said the quake, which struck
at 4:25 p.m. (0717GMT), registered an intensity of three on a
Japanese scale of seven in Nara, 378 kilometers (236 miles) west of
Tokyo.
	   The tremor was strong enough to rattle windows.
	   The agency placed the focus of the quake 60 kilometers (36
miles) underground near Nara.
