<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Switzerland-Bank Deal </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Credit Suisse agrees to take over Brazil's Garantia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) _ Credit Suisse Group announced
Wednesday it has agreed to buy Brazilian investment bank Banco de
Investimentos Garantia for dlrs 675 million.
	   Garantia, Brazil's biggest investment bank with some 320
employees, will become a subsidiary of Credit Suisse First Boston,
the group said in a statement.
	   Credit Suisse said it will pay dlrs 200 million in cash and dlrs
475 million in stock for the bank, which will be renamed Credit
Suisse First Boston Garantia.
	   The transaction is contingent on regulatory approval. It is
expected to close at the end of July.
	   The acquisition ``further enhances CSFB's position as a world
leader in the investment banking industry,'' according to Lukas
Muehlemann, chief executive officer of Credit Suisse.
	   Garantia's book value is put at dlrs 400 million.
 &UR; (dj-gm)
</TEXT>
