<HEADLINE>
Seventy-nine drown in bathing accidents since May
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) - At least 79 people have drowned in Ukraine
since the start of the summer bathing season, officials said
Wednesday.
	   Twelve drowning deaths were registered over the last 10 days of
May and another 67 so far in June, the Emergency Situations
Ministry said. Twelve of the victims in June were children, it
said.
	   About half of the deaths involved drunken people. The ministry
said the rest were caused by neglect for safety, especially that of
children swimming in rivers, lakes and the sea.
