<SLUG> BC-Sports-Cricket-Sri Lanka-New Zealand, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
New Zealand gets Jayasuriya out before lunch
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with lunchtime score. No Pick Up.
 &UR; WITH Sports-Cricket-Sri Lanka-New Zealand-Scoreboard

<TEXT>
	   COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) _ New Zealand captured the prized wicket
of Sanath Jayasuriya to leave Sri Lanka on 52 for one wicket at
lunch on day one of the third test in Colombo on Wednesday.
	   Jayasuriya fell in the ninth over when paceman Chris Cairns had
him edge a ball to second slip, where Bryan Young took a simple
catch.
	   At the crease were Marvan Atapattu on 22 and Mahela Jayawardena
on 16. Sri Lanka won the toss and decided to bat first.
	   The Indian Ocean islanders retained the same side which won the
second Test by an innings, squaring the 3-match series 1-1.
	   New Zealand brought in left-arm spinner Mark Priest to replace
paceman Shyane O'Conner, while also leaving out allrounder Chris
Harris in favor of batsman Craig Spearman.
	   The match started an hour late due to rain.
	   Sri Lanka: Arjuna Ranatunga (capt.), Sanath Jayasuriya, Marvan
Atapattu, Mahela Jayawardena, Aravinda de Silva, Hashan
Tillekeratne, Romesh Kaluwitharana, Kumar Dharmasena, Pramodya
Wickremasinghe, Niroshan Bandaratilleke, Muttiah Muralitharan.
	   New Zealand: Stephen Fleming (capt.), Bryan Young, Mathew Horne,
Nathan Astle, Craig McMillan, Craig Spearman, Adam Parore, Chris
Cairns, Mark Priest, Daniel Vettori, Paul Wiseman.
	   Umpires: Peter Manuel (Sri Lanka), B.K. Ramaswamy (India).
	   Third umpire: Ignatius Anandappa (Sri Lanka).
	   Match Referee: Talat Ali (Pakistan).
