<SLUG> BC-Romania-Bestiality </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police seized 1,500 video tapes with images of bestiality
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: NOTE content. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ Police seized 1,500 video tapes of
people engaging in obscene acts with animals in northwestern
Transylvania, a police officer said Wednesday.
	   An Italian and a Romanian brought the tapes to customs officers
Tuesday, requesting an export license, Col. Constantin Aurel Tufaru
of Timis county police said by telephone. The two were arrested and
the cassettes seized when officers became aware of the content.
	   Experts are investigating if the tapes were filmed in Romania or
only copied.
	   Both Amato Giuseppe an Italian citizen and Cilica Camelia
Adrian, of Lugoj, 350 kilometers (219 miles) northwest of
Bucharest, were released pending further investigation.
	   Romanian law punishes production or distribution of pornographic
or bestial films with between 6 month and 4 years in prison.
	   (ma/amb)
