</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Singapore dollar, stock market tumbles to 7-year low
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with index hitting 7-year low, markets closed, RECASTS
throughout.
 &UR; By LAURINDA KEYS &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   SINGAPORE (AP) _ Fearing the local economy is worse than the
government admits, foreign sellers bailed out of the Singapore
markets in a frenzy Wednesday, and the benchmark index plunged 4.4
percent to its lowest level in seven years.
	   The key Straits Times Industrial Index easily breached a key
support level of 1100 in early trading and fell 49 points to close
at 1067.81, a seven-year low.
