<SLUG> BC-Singapore-Markets, 2nd Ld-1st Add </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
URGENT
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; SINGAPORE: seven-year low.

<TEXT>
	   The Singapore dollar also hit a four-month low against the U.S.
currency.
	   The index's previous low this year was on Jan. 12, when it hit
1073.47 in what was considered the peak of the regional economic
crisis.
	   But fears are growing that Singapore, a hub for transferring
money into, out of, and around the financially weak region, is now
set to suffer more of the consequences of the Asian economic
crisis. It largely sailed unscathed through most of the tumult last
year.
	   Government television attributed Wednesday's market plunge to
heavy selling of the Japanese and Hong Kong currencies amid fears
of more devaluation in the region.
	   The Singapore dollar wasn't spared either, breaking through the
1.72 level against the U.S dollar for the first time since early
February. The U.S. dollar was quoted at a four-month high of 1.7215
Singapore dollars in morning trading, but the currency fluctuated
within one Singapore cent throughout the day.
