<SLUG> BC-Bangladesh-Flood,0124 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Floods inundate homes, injure 15 in Bangladesh
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) _ Torrential rains and rushing rainwater
from hills in neighboring India have flooded Bangladesh's eastern
Sylhet district, inundating homes and vast areas of standing crops,
officials said Wednesday.
	   Fifteen people were injured in the floods that washed away 300
mud-and-straw dwellings and uprooted trees and electric poles.
Water entered thousands of homes in several parts of the district.
	   Power supply and communication within the district was
disrupted.
	   Rivers in Sylhet, 190 kilometers (120 miles) east of the
national capital Dhaka, were flowing above the danger marks,
officials of the Water Development Board said. 	   
</TEXT>
