<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Italy-Ravanelli,0263 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Italy asks FIFA to replace sick striker
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SENLIS, France (AP) _ With striker Fabrizio Ravanelli suffering
from an infection in his right lung, Italy has formally applied to
FIFA to replace him on the team roster with Parma forward Enrico
Chiesa, an official said Wednesday.
	   ``On the basis of the doctor's report, coach Cesare Maldini
decided to begin the proper steps to have FIFA authorize the
replacement of Ravanelli with Chiesa on the Italian team,''
federation spokesman Stefano Balducci said.
	   All the necessary documentation has been filed with soccer's
governing body, he said.
	   Ravanelli was responding well to treatment, but will require a
rest period of at least a week to avoid the danger of developing
full-blown pneumonia, Balducci said.
	   Suffering from fever and cough, he was taken to the hospital in
nearby Creil on Tuesday. He will remain at the team's base camp for
possible examination by FIFA doctors, Balducci said.
	   Regulations allow for last-minute changes among sick or injured
players until 1530 GMT, the kickoff time of the inaugural World Cup
match between Brazil and Scotland.
	   Chiesa is already in the Italian camp as the 23rd player.
	   He had been put on alert as a substitute for forward Alessandro
Del Piero, who has just recovered from a right thigh strain, and
then for Moreno Torricelli, who bruised his foot last week but
resumed practicing Tuesday. Now Chiesa has a third chance to stay
with the team.
	   (pv-sl)
</TEXT>
