<HEADLINE>
Palestinian stabbed to death; Israeli co-worker suspected
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ A Palestinian worker was stabbed to death in a
Jewish settlement in the West Bank on Wednesday, apparently by his
Israeli co-worker, police said.
	   The motive for the killing was not yet known, police spokeswoman
Linda Menuhin said.
	   Both workers were employed by an Israeli truck owner who
delivers soft drinks to settlements in the West Bank.
