<HEADLINE>
Thailand transvestites preying on Japanese tourists
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Two suspected members of a Thai
transvestite gang that targets and robs Japanese tourists have been
arrested and charged with attempted robbery, police said Wednesday.
	   Prachak Trinate, a transvestite, and Sakchai Sae-ung, his
driver, were arrested Sunday in downtown Bangkok by tourist police
as they were trying to convince a Japanese man to go for a ride in
Sakchai's taxi.
	   Transvestite robbers frequently flirt with their potential
victims and then encourage them to get in a taxi driven by an
accomplice, said the police officer who spoke only on condition of
anonymity.
	   ``For some reason the transvestites find Japanese easy to
fool,'' said the officer.
	   In the past year, tourist police have logged over 40 cases
involving the gang, of which all except two victims were Japanese
men, the officer said.
	   He said sometimes the transvestites pretend to be lost and ask
their victim to take them to a certain destination. Once in the
cab, the robbery takes place.
	   The robbers immediately change clothes or hair styles after the
crime, the officer said.
</TEXT>
