<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Kuwait-Mistaken Identities, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Some Kuwait students think Madeleine Albright is an actress
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: RESTORES name of newspaper in 2nd graf; CORRECTS style for
rock 'n' roll in 6th graf &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KUWAIT (AP) _ Some university students in Kuwait think U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is a Hollywood star and
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl is a rock singer, a newspaper
reported Wednesday.
	   The Al-Rai Al-Amm daily said it quizzed 100 students from
different departments of Kuwait University to test their general
knowledge and came up with ``catastrophic'' results.
	   Students were given multiple choices to identify 32 local, Arab
and international personalities including politicians, discoverers,
writers, and artists.
	   While Ahlam, the singer from neighboring United Arab Emirates,
did very well with all students getting the right answer, 45 of the
respondents thought Albright is an American actress. Thirty-one got
her profession right and 24 said there is no such personality.
	   U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan did not fare much better: 59
students said he played soccer for Cameroon. Thirteen said he was a
Communist activist while 23 students identified him correctly. Five
didn't answer at all.
	   Chancellor Kohl was identified by 71 students as a rock 'n' roll
singer, 16 said he is a golf player, four said he was head of state
and nine didn't know.
	   Syrian poet Adonis came out worst: 87 branded him an
international terrorist.
 &UR; de/vj
</TEXT>
