<HEADLINE>
Dollar up, gold down
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar rose was mostly higher against
other major currencies in early European trading Wednesday. Gold
prices fell.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Tuesday:
	   _1.7830 German marks, up from 1.7800
	   _140.48 Japanese yen, up from 140.15
	   _1.4744 Swiss francs, down from 1.4769
	   _5.9792 French francs, up from 5.9695
	   _2.0098 Dutch guilders, up from 2.0066
	   _1,756.75 Italian lire, up from 1,753.50
	   _1.4630 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4598
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6360, up from dlrs
1.6347.
	   London dealers fixed a recommended gold price of dlrs 294.15 bid
per troy ounce at midmorning, down from the closing price of dlrs
296.00 bid Tuesday.
	   In Zurich gold traded at dlrs 294.60, down from dlrs 298.10.
	   Gold fell dlrs 2.80 in Hong Kong to dlrs 292.25.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 5.30 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 5.38.
