<HEADLINE>
Football star Stan Collymore apologizes for fracas with TV
</HEADLINE>
personality Ulrika Jonsson
 &UR; EDS: UPDATES with police saying they are not investigating

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Football star Stan Collymore has apologized for
punching and kicking his girlfriend Ulrika Jonsson in a Paris bar,
but she says the relationship is over.
	   Jonsson, 30, a Swedish-born television personality, returned to
her home in Cookham Dean, 25 miles (40 kms) northwest of London,
following the incident Monday night.
	   ``I would like everyone to know that I am fine and I confirm
that my relationship with Stan Collymore is now over,'' she said in
a statement read to reporters by her agent Wednesday.
	   Police in Paris said they had not been notified of the incident
and were not investigating.
	   Collymore's adviser, graf 3
