<SLUG> BC-Russia-Railroads </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russian railroads to stop carrying military cargo due to
</HEADLINE>
nonpayment &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian railroads will suspend shipments of
military cargo starting Thursday because of the military's chronic
failure to pay its transportation bills, the Railways Ministry
announced.
	   By the start of this month, the army's and security agencies'
debt to the railroads had reached 2.3 billion rubles (dlrs 391
million), the ministry said Wednesday, according to the ITAR-Tass
news agency.
	   However, the suspension will not apply to ``strategically
important cargo ensuring Russia's defense,'' the report said. It
did not elaborate.
	   Russia's cash-strapped railroads are among the nation's chronic
tax debtors, and railroad officials blamed their financial troubles
on the military's failure to pay its bills.
	   (ad/ml)
</TEXT>
