<SLUG> BC-Russia-Crash </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russian combat jet crashes, killing two
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A Russian combat jet crashed Wednesday while
attempting to land in northwestern Russia, killing its crew of two,
officials said.
	   The Su-24 bomber belonging to the Baltic Fleet's air arm crashed
while approaching an air base near the town of Ostrov in the
northwestern Pskov region, the Interfax news agency reported,
quoting fleet officials.
	   Both the pilot and navigator died in the crash.
	   The Su-24 is a twin-engine tactical bomber capable of flying at
supersonic speed.
	   It wasn't immediately clear what caused the crash. Officials
have started an investigation.
	   Many previous accidents with military aircraft have been blamed
on human error. Authorities say pilots' skills have deteriorated
because of a lack of practice caused by the military's severe fund
shortage.
	   (vi/ml)
</TEXT>
