<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Romania-Rescuer </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Belgian man saves three after car slides into a canal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ A Belgian citizen has rescued and
resuscitated three Romanians after their car slid into the waters
of a Transylvanian fish farm, a local official said Wednesday.
	   ``We have never seen something like this here until now, ''
Sorin Daut mayor, of the village Feldioara, said by telephone.
	   He said three people were trapped for several minutes Tuesday
after their car spun out of control and sank into a man-made canal
of a fish farm near Feldioara, 150 kilometers (94 miles) northwest
of Bucharest.
	   Belgian Fanica Bordinc, 30, on holiday in his country of birth,
witnessed the accident from a distance. He then dived into the
waters and, after failing to open the car doors, winched the car
out of the canal with a cable attached to his own car.
	   Bordinc smashed the car windows, pulled out the occupants and
conducted mouth to mouth resuscitation on all three.
	   One victim was recovering in hospital while the other two were
released after a brief medical check.
	   (ma/amb/rp)
</TEXT>
