<HEADLINE>
Eritrea seeks African help to end conflict with Ethiopia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ Eritrea wants mediation by Egypt and other
African nation to end its territorial dispute with Ethiopia that
has turned into war, an Eritrean envoy said Wednesday.
	   ``Both Eritrea and Ethiopia have good relations with Egypt,''
which should facilitate Egyptian mediation between the two
neighbors,'' Abdullah Mahmoud Jaber, an adviser to Eritrean
President Isaias Afwerki, told reporters.
	   He earlier met with President Hosni Mubarak, and said the
Egyptian leader promised to ``play his role to prevent the African
Horn region from exploding.''
	   The dispute between Eritrea and Ethiopia is over a swath of land
that both claim.
	   Border skirmishes broke out on May 6 when Ethiopia accused
Eritrea of incursions. Ethiopian warplanes bombed an Eritrean
military airport in the capital, Asmara, on Friday and Saturday,
touching off serious hostilities.
	   Rwandan and U.S. mediators have proposed a peace plan that
Ethiopia has accepted. Eritrea says it the proposal is too sketchy.
