<SLUG> BC-Turkey-France </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Turkey excludes French firm from major defense deal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ANKARA, Turkey (AP) _ Turkey has excluded a major French defense
firm from a dlrs 150 million tender for aircraft in retaliation for
a motion by French deputies recognizing the alleged Armenian
genocide, a newspaper reported Wednesday.
	   Turkey denies that the deaths of some 1.5 million Armenians
between 1915 and 1923 constituted genocide, insisting that losses
occurred on both sides as the result of a civil war.
	   The English-language Turkish Daily News said that Turkish
defense authorities would not invite Thomson CSF to bid for the
navy aircraft if the French Senate goes on to approve the motion.
	   French deputies in the lower chamber unanimously adopted a
one-sentence motion last month, stating: ``France officially
recognizes the Armenian genocide of 1915.''
	   The defense ministry refused to comment on the report. Thomson
CSF representatives were not immediately available for comment.
	   U.S. firms, Argos Systems and Boeing Co. and Spain's
Construcciones Aeronauticas SA (CASA) were expected to compete for
the bid later this year.
	   Last week, the municipality of Turkey's Aegean port city of
Izmir said it would bar French firms from bidding for a subway
construction project.
	   (ht-fd)
</TEXT>
