r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Philippines-Eritrea     06-10 0152
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Philippines-Eritrea </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ramos: Philippines to evacuate 78 Filipinos from Eritrea
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MANILA, Philippines (AP) _ The Philippines will evacuate 78
Filipino teachers and engineers from Eritrea to escape violence
caused by its border conflict with Ethiopia, President Fidel Ramos
said Wednesday.
	   Ramos said the evacuees will stay temporarily in Jiddah, Saudi
Arabia. He did not say whether they will be sent home or be allowed
to return to Eritrea when the violence there subsides.
	   Ethiopia says Eritrea set off the border conflict on May 6 when
it moved into Ethiopian territory.
	   A peace proposal put forward by the United States and Rwanda
includes a recommendation that Eritrea withdraw to positions it
held prior to May 6.
	   Ethiopia accepted the arrangement in principle, but Eritrea said
it needed work.
	   Ramos did not say if there were Filipinos in Ethiopia.
</TEXT>
