<SLUG> BC-Russia-Serial Killer </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Man sentenced to death for killing 19 people
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A Siberian man fainted Wednesday when he was
sentenced to death for raping, robbing and stabbing to death 19
people, a news agency said.
	   Vadim Yershov, 25, was sentenced by a military tribunal in the
Siberian city of Krasnoyarsk, according to ITAR-Tass. He faced a
military trial because he had committed the crimes after deserting
from his army unit.
	   Yershov had been on trial since last October.
	   In practice, Russia has suspended carrying out death sentences
although capital punishment remains part of the legal code. The
Council of Europe has called on Russia to abolish capital
punishment as a condition of its membership in the organization.
