<HEADLINE>
Neste four-month profit falls to dlrs 26 million
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HELSINKI, Finland (AP) _ Citing lower crude oil prices, the
Neste oil and gas group said Wednesday that its four-month pretax
profit fell to 139 million markkaa (dlrs 25.7 million) from 284
million markkaa in 1997.
	   Net sales during January to April also dropped, to 13.8 billion
markkaa (dlrs 2.5 billion), from 14.9 billion markkaa during the
same period last year.
	   Neste Group, Finland's second-largest company in terms of net
sales, said it was also hit by the economic crisis in Asia, but
expected an improvement in performance during the rest of the year.
	   ``Although the low crude oil price continues to affect Neste's
profitability, the group's running business operations are
estimated to be considerably better in 1998 than in 1997,'' the
company said in a statement.
	   In 1997, Neste's pretax profit increased by 73 percent to 983
million markkaa (dlrs 182 million).
	   Last year, Neste announced that it will sell its 50-percent
holding in Borealis, Europe's largest manufacturer of polyolefins
to the Austrian oil and gas company OMV and the International
Petroleum Investment Company of Abu Dhabi. The sale, worth 4
billion markkaa (dlrs 740 million), will give each company a
25-percent share in Borealis.
	   Neste, which is more than 90-percent state-owned, is active in
oil refining, energy and chemicals. It employs 9,000 people in more
than 30 countries.
	   (mhh-yl)
