<SLUG> BC-Poland-Gelatin Ban </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ban on beef gelatin imports lifted as of July 1
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WARSAW, Poland (AP) _ The government has decided to lift a
6-months-old ban on beef gelatin imports from the European Union,
effective July 1.
	   At a session late Tuesday, the government decided not to extend
the temporary ban which is in force until June 30. But import
certificates will be checked at border crossings to eliminate
imports from countries which had cases of the deadly mad cow
disease, a government statement said.
	   On Jan. 1 the Solidarity-led government of Jerzy Buzek
introduced a ban on all EU gelatin imports, after experts said it
may cause the disease.
	   The ban on all gelatin except beef was lifted Feb. 17, following
media criticism that Poland's main gelatin producer profited from
the situation.
