<HEADLINE>
Spanish authorities seize four tons of hashish in southern Spain
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HUELVA, Spain (AP) _ About four tons of hashish were seized
Wednesday from a Portuguese boat in waters off this southwestern
port, local authorities said.
	   The boat, the Sotovento, was seized after the maritime customs
agents boarded the vessel and discovered 150 bundles of hashish,
said Antonio Sotelo, spokesman for the local interior ministry.
	   Six people on the boat _ nationalities and identities were not
available _ were arrested on smuggling charges, Sotelo said.
	   Spain's southern shore is a major entry point for hashish being
smuggled into Europe.
