<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Britain-Spice Girls </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spice Girls reveal communication with estranged member
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The Spice Girls say they have talked with Geri
Halliwell, better known as Ginger Spice, since her controversial
departure from the band two weeks ago and that they wish her well.
	   They also hastened to assure their audiences that the rocking
and rolling will continue _ even minus one Spice.
	   ``Of course we've been in touch with her _ there's a lot of
things to sort out,'' Sporty Spice Melanie Chisholm said Tuesday
from Italy, where the band teamed up with Luciano Pavarotti for a
charity concert. ``We really do wish her well _ we want her to
succeed.''
	   Halliwell announced she was leaving the all-girl group ``because
of differences between us'' in a statement read by her lawyer May
31. She wished the four other Spices a successful future together
and left her audiences with the playful warning, ``P.S. I'll be
back.''
	   The four other members of the group that topped the charts with
the hit single ``Wannabe'' emphasized Tuesday that band turnover is
a reality of the profession.
	   ``OK, there's been a change in the lineup, but we're not the
first or the last people for that to happen to,'' Chisholm said.
	   ``We are sorry for our fans who've had to go through this, but
we know we are better than ever and there's loads to look forward
to,'' said Baby Spice Emma Bunton.
	   Scary Spice Melanie Brown said, ``I think our next album will be
better vocally. You have to turn a negative into a positive because
it's so easy to be negative.''
	   Posh Spice Victoria Adams said the four Spices are still on good
terms with Halliwell.
	   ``If Geri walked through the door now we would all be like,
`hello,' '' she said. ``It would be like friends meeting up. It's
not nasty, we've all said that. We all love each other and we all
love Geri.''
	   The Spice Girls are scheduled to tour the United States
beginning June 14 and said they will record their third album later
this year.
	   (jh-kg)
</TEXT>
