<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Armenia-Bus </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Second person dies as a result of bus fire in Armenia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   YEREVAN, Armenia (AP) _ A 12-year-old boy died in a hospital on
Wednesday, the second victim of a bus fire that badly burned more
than 20 schoolchildren, officials said.
	   Sarkis Khachatrian died of severe burns in the Yerevan Central
Hospital. The first victim died in the hospital on Monday, and
several other children are in grave condition, hospital officials
said.
	   The bus carrying 40 students, teachers and parents returning
from a picnic exploded and burst into flames on a country road near
the village of Bartsrashen, 30 kilometers (19 miles) south of
Yerevan, on Sunday.
	   Officials said the explosion was apparently caused by a gas
leak.
	   Most buses and other vehicles in Armenia run on natural gas.
Gasoline is in short supply due to an economic blockade imposed by
neighboring Azerbaijan because of the territorial conflict over
Nagorno-Karabakh.
	   (str/vi/ls) 	   
</TEXT>
