<HEADLINE>
Streamlining insurance operations with Genius, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Streamlining insurance operations with Genius, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Nur Aida MustaffaASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   SOFTWARE developer Rebus International (Asia) Sdn Bhd has
launched its latest insurance solution which incorporates new
features for facilitating insurance agents in their work.
	   The General Insurance Underwriting System (Genius) offers
value-added features which include the different insurance
products, distribution channels, information, contain costs,
implementation and maintenance, according to the company.
	   Rebus added that the solution can deal with all classes of
non-life personal and commercial insurance schemes such as fire,
motor, accident and engineering.
	   According to Rebus Asia's managing director David Waring, there
are four aspects of Genius which differentiate it from other
insurance software available in the market. These are its model
base, product definition, name database, diary and management
information.
	   The features are taken from Rebus Asia's previous products which
were also targeted at insurance companies. ``The additional
features make the software more flexible and user-friendly,'' said
Waring.
	   He said the model base is designed as a package to handle a wide
variety of business. It can be easily customised to the particular
requirements of a company, he said.
	   Waring added that existing users from any class of business such
as household, liability, life and health insurance, medical
malpractice and inwards reinsurance are handled within the same
system.
	   ``This kind of flexibility is controlled through the product
definition which allows the users to select from the many possible
processing and data elements that are required to make up a
policy,'' he said.
	   Genius, Waring said, is designed to be used worldwide either as
a single installation for a small company or as branch operations
for multinational corporations (MNCs).
	   ``To ensure that it can be used worldwide, this software allows
flexibility in terms of language and currency,'' he said,
explaining that Genius is able to do so as the screen and print
images can be translated with no programming changes. He claimed
that users can also set up their own base currency using the
system.
	   Waring said the product definition allows each insurance company
to tailor the package to suit their own requirements. For instance,
a company which specialises in one type of package may only require
a single product, whereas another company that writes a wide range
of general business may set up as many products as required.
	   Rebus Asia offers a few pricing options for customers who want
to purchase Genius. For instance, the price for a 10-user system
can start from RM300,000.
	   ``We also offer rental option which is about RM120,000 a year,''
Waring said, adding that the company, however, understands the
current economic condition and is willing to share the burden with
other insurance companies.
	   ``As we are committed in this region for the long haul, we offer
users several ways of settling payments. One way is to link payment
and the product with the performance of an insurance company.''
	   
</TEXT>
