<HEADLINE>
New challenging courses for golf, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
New challenging courses for golf, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Lim Chong GheeASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   GOLF simulation games are not everybody's favourite. Those who
love golf simulation games are mostly golfers in real life. But
then again, there are also those who just love the game for the
gameplay and the stunning simulation technology the developers have
incorporated into it.
	   The latest release from Access Software, a golf simulation game
called Links LS '98 is one example of good gameplay and stunning
graphics. Links LS' predecessor Links 386 was one of the best
computer golf games a while ago. This long-awaited next-generation
version features stunning visuals and superb realism.
	   Links LS '98 (LS stands for Legends in Sports) comes with
courses designed by one of the best golf players in golf history,
Arnold Palmer.
	   It comes with four different real-life resort courses such as
The Kapalua Plantation, Bay and Village courses in the island of
Maui, Hawaii, and the Latrobe Country Course Club in Pennsylvania,
US. It is also a complete 72- hole golf championship course.
	   The original package comes with four compact disks (CDs) and a
complete reference manual (an advantage of getting original
software). The CDs include four courses, fly-by views of all holes,
six different golfer animations, virtual reality tour of the
resorts, video tour of the courses and even interviews and the
biodata of Arnold Palmer and his father Deacon Palmer.
	   Links LS comes with unlimited screen resolutions with up to 16.7
million colours. It will definitely make use of the extra random
access memory in your graphic card.
	   The background graphics on these courses are outstanding. Though
the scenery is digitised, there is a distinct realism that beats
the rest. It even comes with animations such as the fluttering of
flags and even flying planes, helicopters and blimps scuttling
across the course.
	   When you play near a water hazard, you will be dazzled with the
reflection of surrounding trees, terrains and even the clouds.
	   There are six golfers which include Arnold Palmer as well as
three other men and two women golfers. Each of these golfers has
different appearances and skills. However, only Arnold Palmer is
controlled by the game.
	   Nonetheless, Links LS allows you to create players either for
computer- controlled golfers or human-controlled golfers.
	   One of the most significant abilities of this game is that you
can play at the main view window and have up to eight windows to
view your shots.
	   You have forward and reverse landing cameras, a Golfer cam, Pin
cam, Green cam, Putting cam, Side Cam, Top cam, Profile and even
chat! Most of these cameras are ``smart cams'' and will follow your
every shot.
	   And these cameras are adjustable from one foot to about 100 feet
off the ground. If you are used to the working environment of
Windows 95, you won't have a problem in handling all of them at
once. These cams are great in a sense that it allows you to see how
and where your shot is going and to learn what went wrong. Now, if
it is your first time on the course, you can even have a fly-by
view of the hole. How nice if it happens in real life! Links LS
gives you control over your shots from adjusting your stance,
position of the ball, club face to controlling your swing. In Links
LS, you can even configure and save your swings so that it can be
used again and again. The swing control is based on the three-click
swing.
	   There is even a feature in Links LS that allows you to rotate
from your original position when making a difficult shot. This is a
real treat and can be very helpful when you are stuck in the woods.
Once my tee off shot landed right behind a big oak tree facing the
green, and without this rotating feature, I wouldn't be able to get
out of the maze, don't think pros can get out of it either.
	   Besides the lie and wind indicators, similar to all golf
simulations, there is also a slope indicator. This indicator is
very useful as it tells you the slope your ball is currently
resting on. It is very helpful, especially on the green.
	   Enough of the features. let's explore the courses. The Kapalua
Bay, Village and Plantation course is situated in the paradise
island of Maui.
	   The name ``Kapalua'' means ``arms that reach out'', referring to
the bay of the island.
	   The Kapalua Village Course was designed by Arnold Palmer and Ed
Seay.
	   This Par 71 championship course is both a challenging and an
enjoyable course. It is also the home for the Lincoln Mercury
International Championship, one of the most acclaimed post-PGA
tours. It started in 1982 with the prize money of just over
US$15,000 to a staggering US$150,000 in the 90s. Many great golfers
such as Greg Norman and Fred Couples have won their games here in
the past. It is also a 7,263-yard Par 73 championship golf course.
	   This is a very challenging course which has the aspect of an
ancient Scottish golf course - golfing at a grand scale.
	   According to the preview, this course will get you to use
practically almost every club in your bag.
	   The Latrobe Country Course is situated at the backyard of Arnold
Palmer's home in Pennsylvania. This 18-hole course was built on
scenic highlands and surrounded with beautiful trees. The club was
founded in 1920 and had its first nine holes in the following year.
The building of the first nine holes involved Deacon Palmer. And by
1963, this nine-hole course was expanded into an 18-hole
championship golf course.
	   This title deserves a big thumb's-up. Everything in Links LS is
precise and professional. If you are looking for a challenging and
an advanced golf game, this is a must-get software. It also comes
with Internet-play where you can challenge golfers from all around
the world.
	   This is the type of game that will give you plenty to talk about
with your golf-crazy friends. Grab it now and check it out
yourself.
	   
</TEXT>
