<HEADLINE>
Sabah Foundation takes the top honours at Dragon Boat Festival, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Sabah Foundation takes the top honours at Dragon Boat Festival, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Joniston BangkuaiASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA KINABALU, Sun. - Sabah Foundation edged six other teams to
win the Governor's Trophy in the international men's open category
of the annual Sabah Dragon Boat Festival at Likas Bay today.
	   Posting a record time of 3 minutes 8.2 seconds, they received
medals and cash prize of RM4,000.
	   Second and third were Oriental Bank and Persatuan Lumba Perahu
Negara Brunei Darussalam with a time of 3:8.37 and 3:10.0
respectively.
	   Sabah Foundation also won the mixed team event to clinch the
Mount Kinabalu Trophy and RM2,500 cash prize as well as the Darwin
Challenge Special Trophy.
	   The international corporate category was won by DBNT Darwin of
Australia in 3:19.1. They received the Sabah Dragon Trophy and a
cash prize of RM3,000.
	   Perwira Nusantara Mengkabong won the Chief Minister's Trophy in
3:02.07 and received a cash prize of RM2,500. Darau Butterfly and
Sri Wawasan Binsulok finished second and third respectively.
	   In the men's category for the Sabah Chinese Cultural Association
(SCCA) President's Trophy, Kampung Nelayan emerged champion with a
time of 3:4.4.
	   They also received RM2,500.
	   The women's category for the SCCA President's Trophy was won by
Wanita Nusantara Mengakabong with a time of 2:56.5. They also
received RM2,500.
	   Persatuan Kenu Sabah won the Mount Trusmadi Trophy for the
student's category and received a prize of RM2,500.
	   The Yang di-Pertua Negeri Tun Sakaran Dandai gave away the
prizes.
	   Jointly organised by the Sabah Tourism Promotion Corporation and
the SCCA, the event was held to promote the State as a tourism
destination.
	   
</TEXT>
