<SLUG> BC-NATO-Kosovo-Protest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Albania's protest to demand NATO intervention in Kosovo
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With NATO-Kosovo, Yugoslavia-Kosovo &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos BRU101-103 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) _ Hundreds of Albanians protested outside
NATO headquarters Wednesday to demand the Western alliance
intervene to stop Serbian military action in Kosovo.
	   ``If NATO doesn't take the decision to intervene as fast as
possible, we fear that the number of victims will increase,''
organizer Ramadan Gashi told Associated Press Television.
	   The demonstration came on the eve of a meeting of NATO defense
ministers are expected to consider plans for possible intervention,
including perhaps sending in troops, air strikes or a no-fly zone
over Kosovo.
	   Some 300 protesters took part in the demonstration organized by
the Albanian Community in Belgium. Many waved the red-and-black
Albanian flag or others carried banners. One read ``Nothing learned
from Bosnia?''
	   The demonstration was in solidarity with a a protest by some
20,000 ethnic Albanians in the provincial capital Pristina. The
organizers said Albanians living in Washington, Ottawa and capitals
around Europe were also planning protests.
 &UR; (pa)
</TEXT>
