<HEADLINE>
Council beats Pressmen in bowling, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Council beats Pressmen in bowling, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MORE than 60 participants from the Seremban Municipal Council
and Negri Sembilan Press Club or Kelana pitted their skills against
each other during a bowling tournament at the Seremban Parade
Golden Bowl recently.
	   The tournament was officiated at by Menteri Besar and MPS
president Tan Sri Mohamad Isa Abdul Samad, who led the councillors
to overall victory over the Pressmen after three frames.
	   Mohamad Isa's team also took second spot in the three-man team
event partnering municipal councillors Badaruddin Ahmad and Md Nor
Said with a total score of 1,188 points.
	   The winners of the event went to Kelana's trio of Kamarulzaman
Salleh (New Straits Times), Meor Harman Shakri (Utusan Malaysia)
and Chua Eng Chuan (Guang Ming) who scored 1,206 points.
	   In third place was the council's team represented by Ruslly
Baharom, Faridah Zainuddin and Lee Fook Moi with 1,179 points.
	   The tournament which was divided into team trios, men's and
women's individual events also saw Ruslly clinching the men's
individual title with a total score of 516 points.
	   Ramli Harun of Kelana took the second spot in the men's
individual event with a total 461 points while Badaruddin Ahmad
from the council took third placing with 446 points.
	   Women bowlers from the council swept the top three places in the
single's event with Noriza Matsham emerging the champion with 407
points, Faridah Zainuddin in second place with 375 points and Siti
Fatimah Wahab taking the third spot with 372 points.
	   
</TEXT>
