	   MONDAY, June 1 DEPUTY Prime Minister Datuk Seri Anwar Ibrahim
said the domestic interest rates must remain firm since offshore
ringgit deposits rates now stood at about 20 per cent.
	   TONGKAH Holdings Bhd intends to dispose its entire 51 per cent
interest in Tongkah Medivest Sdn Bhd to Hospital Pantai Bhd for
RM35.7 million cash.
	   TUESDAY, June 2 PRIME Minister Datuk Seri Dr Mahathir Mohamad
said Malaysia and East Asian countries need a revival of Japanese
investments to revitalise their troubled economies.
	   PRINTING company Tien Wah Press Holdings Bhd has tied up with
Interbobbin (UK) Ltd, to produce cigarette filter covers.
	   WEDNESDAY, June 3 MALAYSIA has registered a trade suplus of
RM12.4 billion for January to April this year, the Statistics
Department announced.
	   CYGAL Bhd said it has applied to the Kuala Lumpur High Court on
March 21 to strike out the petition filed by Syarikat Lian Ping
Enterprise Sdn Bhd to wind up Cygal over non-payment of RM3.2
million.
	   THURSDAY, June 4 PENGURUSAN Danaharta Nasional Bhd, expected to
need RM25 billion and would initially issue RM10 billion in bonds,
AMC chief executive officer Azman Yahya said.
	   METAL Reclamation Bhd, which opened at RM2.01 and closed at
2.03, registered a 21 sen premium on its maiden day on the KLSE
second board.
	   FRIDAY, June 5 THE Securities Commission has withdrawn its
written consent to Halim Securities Sdn Bhd to carry on its
licenced business activity following default proceedings taken by
the Securities Clearing Automated Network Services Sdn Bhd and the
SC's rejection of its proposed corporate restructuring plan.
	   THE Securities Commisssion has revoked the licence of Omega
Securities Sdn Bhd following its failure to come up with a
restructuring exercise.
	   
