<HEADLINE>
More contributions for PC Fair quiz, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
More contributions for PC Fair quiz, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Rosabel Thomas; Shyla SangaranASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MORE attractive prizes await visitors at the coming PC Fair '98
cash-and- carry event.
	   Personal computer (PC) direct marketeer Gateway is giving away
100 units of its famous icon, the spotted cow, worth a total
RM3,000 for the Quiz Time session.
	   To win, one needs only to visit the IT Publications Sdn Bhd
(ITP) booth at all three venues in Johor Baru, Penang and Kuala
Lumpur, and provide correct answers to some questions about Gateway
and its products.
	   ITP, which produces Computimes, will hold the whole quiz session
at the event. Gateway's director of marketing for South Asia Niall
J. O'Reilly handed over the prizes to ITP's marketing executive
Tang Sze Anne in Kuala Lumpur last week.
	   The Johor Baru leg of PC Fair '98 will be held at the Leisure
Mall from June 19 to 21. The Penang and Kuala Lumpur events will
take place from June 26 to 28. For Penang, the venue is the
Geodesic Dome in Komtar while the Kuala Lumpur venue is the Putra
World Trade Centre.
	   Another sponsor for Quiz Time is Tele Dynamics Sdn Bhd, a member
of KUB Group and the local distributor for Toshiba information and
communication systems.
	   The company is giving away 30 Toshiba collared T-shirts for the
Kuala Lumpur leg.
	   The T-shirts, which cost RM20 each, will be distributed to the
winners who can provide the correct answers to questions regarding
Tele Dynamics and its products.
	   Tele Dynamics' senior manager for personal computer, sales and
marketing division Y.S. Ng handed over the prizes to ITP's sales
executive Wan Halim Ismail in Petaling Jaya last week.
	   
</TEXT>
