	   Government yesterday blamed a group of BNP supporters for
blocking the Dhaka-Chittagong highway in Narayanganj by deflating
wheels of buses and trucks leading to a huge traffic jam.
	   ``Police Super of Narayanganj said a terrorist group, led by BNP
leader Noor Hossain, on Monday night put barricades at Simrai in
Siddirganj thana and forcibly tried to capture buses, mini-buses
and trucks on Dhaka-Chittagong and Dhaka-Sylhet highways,'' said an
official handout here.
	   It said the terrorists also unleashed attacks on the vehicles
and their drivers and assaulted some passengers and snatched away
their money and wrist watches.
	   Narayanganj-Demra-Meghna Sarak Paribahan Sramik Committee
president Taher Khan Babu filed a case with Siddirganj thana in
this connection, the handout said.
	   On information, according to the SP, senior police officials in
the district rushed to the spot. But the barricade already created
a huge traffic congestion on Dhaka-Chittagong and Dhaka-Sylhet
highways.
	   Being requested by police, the handout said, Roads and Highways
Department sent a wrecker to the troubled spot but, it could not
reach there due to traffic congestion on both sides of the
barricade.
	   The handout said SP of Narayanganj informed that police in
cooperation with Roads and Highways Department were trying to bring
normalcy on the road.
	   In a similar version, leaders of bus owners' and workers'
associations have blamed local terrorists of BNP for the disruption
and said such acts in the name of political programme is very
unfortunate.
	   They criticised the attack by BNP on innocent passengers and
demanded legal action against the culprits.
	   Signatories to the statement are Purbanchaliyo Malik Oikya Jote
president Ibrahim Chengish, Mini-bus Malik Oikya Jote president M
Mokter Hossain, Narayanganj-Demra-Meghna-Narsingdi Bus, Mini-bus
Malik Samity president Nurul Amin Maksud, Dhaka-Narayanganj Sarak
Paribahan Sramik Union president M Aiyub Ali and its acting
secretary Jilani Mia.
	   
