<HEADLINE>
New pavilion boost for cricket fans, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
New pavilion boost for cricket fans, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Timothy LeonardASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   BUILT at a cost of RM120,000, the new cricket pavilion at Kolej
Tuanku Ja'afar, Mantin is the first of its kind in Negri Sembilan.
	   The pavilion which was opened last Saturday by Tunku Tan Sri
Imran Tuanku Ja'afar is a joint venture between the college and the
Silver State Cricket Club.
	   The college provides the ground and the maintenance while the
club has agreed to bear the cost in consideration for a 10-year
priority use of the pavilion and ground.
	   Last Saturday's opening ceremony was held at the ground after a
25-over friendly cricket match between Tunku Imran's 11 and the
President of Silver State Cricket Club's 11.
	   Tunku Imran, who is a trustee and governor of the college, is
also president of the Malaysian Cricket Association and a keen
supporter of the game.
	   The Silver State Cricket Club was founded in 1991 by Bill
Davidson and has about 40 playing members. It participates actively
in all local competitions at inter-club level. The core players
that make up the team come from Perak, Kuala Lumpur and Negri
Sembilan.
	   ``One of the principal aim of building the pavilion is to
encourage more people to take up cricket as a sport. Since this is
the only place with all the sufficient facilities in the State, I
would urge all those interested in playing cricket to come and join
our club, entitling them to play on the ground for free,'' said
club president Davidson.
	   ``I would also like to extend my sincere thanks and appreciation
to all sponsors, donors and contributers who have made the project
a success.''
	   
</TEXT>
