	   KEN-Air Services beat nine other teams for the second
consecutive year to become champion in the third annual Ansett
Australia Bowl'Em Over finals at Bangsar Bowl recently.
	   Holiday Tours emerged the first runner-up and the third place
went to Bousted Travel.
	   The Ansett Bowl'Em Over clinics were organised by Ansett
Australia for frontline travel agents to offer a fun activity while
provinding an opportunity for the agents to learn a new sport.
	   Seven other teams of five players each who participated in the
finals included top travel agencies in the country - Peter
Stuyvesant Travel, Sime Darby Travel, Deluxe Tours, Gasi Travel,
Sri-America Tours and Falcon Travel.
	   Ansett Australia's country sales manager for Malaysia Henry Goh
said the event was organised to support the country's emphasis on
sports this year.
	   It is also to allow travel industry staff to learn some skills
and socialise.
	   ``The competition was organised in our effort to cultivate
closer ties between the agents while offering an opportunity for
them to learn a new game,'' he said.
	   ``The competition is the culmination of a series of three
bowling clinics held over two weeks and each team had to
participate in at least two clinics to qualify for this final
competition.
	   ``We offer first prize winners a ticket each to Australia and
the first runner-up a ticket each to Jakarta.''
	   The individual men's event was won by Simon Teh of Reliance
Travel and the runner-up was Ricky Liew of Peter Stuyvesant Travel.
	   Maggie Ong of Ken-Air Services emerged champion in the women's
event while the runner-up was Marianne Ho of Bousted Travel.
	   
