	   JOHOR BARU, Sun. - Ninety refurbished Proton cars valued at more
than RM2.5 million were sold by the second day of the three-day EON
Motoria auto fair at Plaza Angsana in Tampoi.
	   Of the number, 34 units were sold on Friday and 56 on Saturday,
EON Motor Ria Sdn Bhd executive director Abdul Razak Dawood said.
	   Response to the fair has been encouraging. The company had
earlier set a sale target of 100 vehicles.
	   Abdul Razak said he expected sales to touch 120 units when the
fair ended tomorrow.
	   EON Motor Ria had sold 636 units of reconditioned Proton Saga,
Proton Saga Iswara and Proton Perdana models worth RM19.7 million
at earlier fairs held in Subang, Ampang, Ipoh, Penang, Wangsa Maju,
Alor Star and Langkawi.
	   
