DSE index declines further, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) trading maintained its downward
trend yesterday . The All Share Price Index retreated by 1.20 per
cent or by 8.1 points to close at 664.73 points from Monday's
672.83 points. The price index had a total loss of 113.73 points
during the last three days at a stretch. The number of gaining and
losing issues stood at 55 and 68 respectively, out of total of 126
issues that changed hands yesterday. Three issues remained
unchanged yesterday. If the trend of gradual increase in the number
of gaining issues remains unchanged, the next session may witness
rise both in the price index and the market capital .
	   However ,a DSE dealer said :Sunday's fall was not a traditional
one .According to him, ``we may not call it even a market
correction. The market correction in a stable market starts after a
big rise in the share value and it maintains gradual decline in the
share prices for couple of days unless any other factors take place
in the trading environment.''Responding to the day's trading, the
turnover of the day declined. A total of, 3,44,713 shares and
debentures valued at Taka 31.94 million were traded against
previous day's 4,07,730 worth Taka 37.80 million, marking a fall by
63017 shares and debentures in volume and Taka 5.86 billion in
value respectively on the day.
	   The market capitalisation of the day declined by 0.73 billion to
day's Taka 59.78 against Monday's Taka 60.51 billion. Singer
Bangladesh Ltd led the losers for having a loss of Taka 229.74 per
share while Bangladesh Lamps Ltd declined by Taka 87.46, Apex Foods
Ltd by Taka 42.11, Aziz Pipes Ltd by Taka 31.39 and IBN Sinha
Pharmaceuticals Ltd by Taka 35.00.Monno Jutex Industries Ltd
advanced by Taka 110.00, Bangladesh Leaf Tobacco Co Ltd by Taka
65.00, AMCL Pran by Taka 19.61 and Libra Pharmaceuticals Ltd by
Taka 13.70.
	   Beximco Pharmaceuticals Ltd emerged as the value leader for
having a transactions of Taka 2.39 million.The share prices of
Beximco Pharmaceuticals was almost static. It stood at Taka 63.29
to its previous day's rate of Taka 63.30.
	   
