<SLUG> BC-Vatican-Ethiopia-Eritrea </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Catholic bishops appeal to their governments for peace
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   VATICAN CITY (AP) _ Roman Catholic bishops from Ethiopia and
Eritrea have appealed to their governments to end their armed
conflict before it turns into an all-out war.
	   They said war will set back economic development and
``destabilize the already delicate political balance in the Horn of
Africa region.''
	   The joint appeal was signed in Addis Ababa, the Ethiopian
capital, Sunday, and released Wednesday by the Vatican.
	   The bishops said they feared the border conflict ``may lead to
an all-out war among brothers and sisters who share a common
history and tradition.''
	   They said they felt ``the urgent duty to make an appeal to our
governments'' before the conflict escalated.
