	   Minister for Post, Telecommunications, Housing and Public Works
Mohammad Nasim yesterday said all districts would be brought under
modern digital network by the year 2000.
	   He was formally inaugurating the 600-line expanded automatic
telephone exchange in Tangail.
	   The minister said the government is considering to hand over the
existing thana telephone exchange to private sector enterprises,
which got licenses earlier to install digital exchanges.
	   State Minister for Foreign Affairs Abul Hasan Chowdhury, Abul
Mannan MP, Abdul Kader Siddiqui Bir Uttam, MP, Khondoker
Asaduzzaman MP, Awami League Central Joint Secretary Shamsur Rahman
Khan Shahajahan and T and T Board Chairman M A Mannan Chowdhury,
among others, spoke on the occasion.
	   Nasim said 3.5 lakh telephone lines were installed in 26 years
since Independence but the present government has given 1.5 lakh
telephone connections across the country.
	   He said the government is putting its best efforts to reach
telephone facilities to every house in the country.
	   
