<HEADLINE>
Israel plans international air show saluting Israeli air force
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Israel plans its first international air show
with aerobatic crews from nine nations, including Jordan and
Turkey, to salute the Israeli Air Force on its 50th anniversary, an
official said Wednesday.
	   Crews will arrive along with their aircraft for the show, which
will be held in the skies over the Mediterranean Sea coast on July
1 and July 3.
	   The pilots and planes will be quartered in Israeli Air Force
bases during their stay, said the official.
	   Other countries participating are France, Poland, Italy,
Britain, Spain, Chile and Switzerland. The air force held its own
air show on Israel's 50th anniversary on April 30.
