<HEADLINE>
RU students demand postponement of exams during World Cup, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
RU students demand postponement of exams during World Cup, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Rajshahi University students brought out a procession Monday
demanding postponement of all examinations during the World Cup,
scheduled to start from today.
	   At least 400 students brought out the procession from the
university library at 10 am and held a meeting in front of the
administrative building.
	   Leaders of different student organisations addressed the
meeting. Later, the students submitted a memorandum to the
Vice-Chancellor.
	   The Vice-Chancellor said he has no power to postpone the
examinations, the holding of examination lies solely with the
respective departments.
	   
