<HEADLINE>
2 lakh people marooned as flood engulfs 5 Sylhet thanas, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
2 lakh people marooned as flood engulfs 5 Sylhet thanas, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   About two lakh people of 300 villages in five thanas of the
district have been marooned by flash floods caused by heavy rain
and onrush of water coming from across the border.
	   The flood-affected thanas are: Goainghat, Companyganj,
Kanaighat, Jaintapur and Jakiganj.
	   Official sources said 47 mm rainfall was recorded in 12 hours
ending at 9 pm Monday.
	   The rivers in the areas were swelling up while the Kushiara was
flowing slightly above the danger level at some points. The Surma
at Amalsid in Jakiganj was also flowing 9 cm above the danger mark.
	   Several hundred acres of land in the thanas with Aus and Aman
crops have been inundated by the water.
	   The road, linking Goainghat thana to the district sadar, has
gone under water disrupting the communication. Telecommunications
in Kanaighat has also remained suspended.
	   In Cox's Bazar, monsoon set in with thundershower taking a toll
of three people dead and five wounded in the district today.
	   Officials said two people drowned in a boat capsize in river
Matamuhuri while another was killed by lightning in Ramu thana.
	   The district experienced 110 mm rainfall in only six hours from
6 am to 12 noon, resulting in inundation of low-lying areas.
	   Besides, gusty wind with a speed of up to 85 kph swept the
coastal district, uprooting many trees.
	   In Ramu thana headquarters, the main road went under knee-deep
water pouring out of the overflowing Bankkhali river.
	   Two people - a 65-year-old man and a boy of 12 years - drowned
as a ferry boat caught in a storm capsized in the Matamuhuri in
Chakaria thana at about 10 am. Eight others on board, however, swam
ashore, police said.
	   In Ramu thana, Zaker Hossain, 35, was killed by lightning while
working at a riverghat.
	   Five women suffered severe injuries as a thunderbolt boomed on
their house at the offshore Shahpurirdwip in Teknaf thana at about
10-30 am.
	   The injured-Sahana Akter, Zaheda Begum, Lanu Begum, Kajal and
Shaheda-were admitted to Teknaf Thana Health Complex.
	   UNB adds: A tornado lashed two villages of Fatikchhari thana of
Chittagong early this morning leaving a man dead and levelling
about 150 houses to the ground.
	   The storm, with a wind speed of about 112 km per hour, struck
Gahira and Azadi villages at 6 am and lasted for seven minutes.
	   Official sources said some 150 kutcha and semi-pucca houses of
the two villages were damaged.
	   Road communications between Khagrachhari and Chittagong remained
cut off as the road was blocked by uprooted trees.
	   
</TEXT>
