<SLUG> HEATWAVE-CLAIMS-3-LIVES sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Heatwave claims 3 lives in Sirajganj, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Heatwave claims 3 lives in Sirajganj, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Three people died from sunstroke in three thanas here during the
last 24 hours till 1 pm today as severe heatwave continued to sweep
the northern district, local sources said.
	   The victims were identified as Abdul Jabbar (60) of Nandina of
Kamarkhand thana, Fazlar Rahman (55) of Hatikamrul of Ullapara
thana and Roushan Ara (40) of Tarakandi of Shahjadpur thana. Jabbar
died from sunstroke when he was working on a paddy field today
while Fazlar, a grocer, fell sick on his way home and died soon
after he was taken to his house.
	   Roushan, a housewife, fainted while she was cooking at her home
at around noon Monday. A patient of high blood pressure, she died
instantaneously.
	   
</TEXT>
