	   An automobile businessman, Mustafizur Rahman Musa (30), arrested
in connection with the killing of Syed Sadequr Rahman Masum, was
remanded for three days yesterday. The court refused him bail.
	   The Detective police produced him before the court of the Chief
Metropolitan Magistrate at about 2:30 pm seeking seven days remand.
	   According to police, Musa was directly involved in the killing
of Masum.
	   On Monday night, a DB police squad, led by assistant
commissioner Golam Kibria, arrested Musa from Tejkunipara.
	   Earlier, Tejgaon police arrested an autorickshaw-driver, Ismail
Mollah, from the same area in connection with the murder of Masum.
He was sent to jail hajat after the end of the four day remand on
June 7.
	   Masum, an official of a garments factory, was shot dead near his
Tejkunipara residence on June 1.
	   
