<SLUG> BC-Norway-Inflation,0103 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Norway's annual inflation rate 2.1 percent in May
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OSLO, Norway (AP) _ Norway's inflation rate fell to 2.1 percent
for the 12 months ending on May 15, from 2.5 percent a month
earlier and 2.7 percent in May 1997, the state statistics agency
announced Wednesday.
	   Statistics Norway said the consumer price index for May was
275.4, compared to 275.8 in April and 269.7 in May 1997. All the
figures use 1979 as a base year with an index of 100.
	   The agency said lower electricity rates and a fall in clothing
prices were among the main reasons for the drop in inflation.
