<SLUG> BC-Russia-Tax Arrest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Yeltsin fires statistics chief arrested in tax scandal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ President Boris Yeltsin fired the head of Russia's
statistics service who was charged with helping big companies evade
taxes, news agencies reported Wednesday.
	   Yuri Yurkov, head of the State Statistics Committee, was
arrested Monday, along with his deputy and up to 20 alleged
accomplices. Police seized dlrs 1.5 million, dlrs 1 million of it
from Yurkov's home.
	   Investigators accused them of manipulating economic data to hide
the real output of companies and reduce their tax liability, and
with selling classified information about rival companies'
performance.
	   The arrests could have far-reaching implications if it turns out
that data government officials rely on to make policy and collect
taxes was falsified.
	   Tax evasion is a major problem in Russia, from ordinary citizens
to large corporations. The government's inability to collect tax
revenues has slowed efforts to boost the economy.
	   (ls) 	   
</TEXT>
