<BODY>
<SLUG> VAST-AREA-OF-LAND sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vast area of land near BJMB under illegal occupation, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
Vast area of land near BJMB under illegal occupation, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   Vast areas of land on both sides of the Iswardi-Sirajganj
railway route near the Bangabandhu Jamuna Multipurpose Bridge
(BJMB) have allegedly been occupied illegally by a section of
influential people . As the day for opening of the long-cherished
bridge is nearing , the unscrupulous and selfish people are waiting
to exploit the full benefit through grabbing the state property
.These people are erecting sheds, semi-pucca and pucca stalls,
shops, houses and even markets on the railway lands much to the
concern of the innocent public. On the other hand, most of the
railway lands from Bhanguria railway station to Boral Ghat and
Boral bridge station to Saratnagar Bazar have been grabbed
illegally by the local people due to negligence of the authorities
concerned, it is alleged.
	   A number of business establishments have been constructed on the
railway lands which have narrowed the roads creating problems for
the general people who travel by trains . Traffic jam is a regular
feature in these areas . About 40,000 acres of railway land worth
about Taka 300 crore are allegedly under the unauthorised
possession of some influential people in the railway's western
zone. As a result the government is deprived of huge amount of
revenue. Meanwhile organised gangs of thugs are stealing the doors,
windows and other valuable property of the railway staff quarters
in the area everyday. This dastardly act should be checked
immediately , as with the opening of the BJMB importance of the
railway station will increase greatly .
	   According to a source of the Paksey western railway estate
office, recovery of the railway property from the clutches of the
illegal occupants is not easy. Permission will have to be sought
from the appropriate authority before eviction of the unauthorised
occupants. The railway authorities launch drive from time to time
to evict the unauthorised occupants , but cannot take action
against them most of the time due to threats and pressures from
vested quarters and political groups. Our Correspondent from
Sirajganj adds: All arrangements have almost completed for opening
of the Bangabandhu Jamuna Multipurpose Bridge (BJMB) on June 23. It
was disclosed at a views exchange meeting on June 3 at the
conference room of the Deputy Commissioner of Sirajganj.
	   The views exchange meeting was presided over by Deputy
Commissioner AKM Shamsuddin and was attended by political leaders,
professionals, journalists and leaders of various socio-cultural
organisations. The Deputy Commissioner informed the meeting that
strict security measures have been taken for opening of the BJMB.
The public meeting at the western part of the bridge at Saidabad is
expected to be attended by about 20 lakh people. The educational
institutions will remain closed to accommodate the guests from 16
northern districts.
	   
</TEXT>
