<HEADLINE>
983 illegal immigrants held from different border points, THE INDEPENDENT
</HEADLINE>
983 illegal immigrants held from different border points, THE INDEPENDENT &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   BANGLADESH
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   A total of 983 illegal immigrants were arrested by the 32nd
Battalion of the Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) from different border
points during the last five months. A total of 234 eases were also
lodged in these connections with different thanas during the
January-May period of the current year. It is gathered from a
source of the 32nd Battalion of BDR at Jhumjhumpur that of the
total arrested illegal immigrants 596 were arrested while entering
into the country from India and 387 were arrested while crossing
the border to India. A total of 132 men , women and children were
arrested in January , 141 in February, 44 in March, 159 in April
and 120 in May 1998.
	   Meanwhile, 57 illegal immigrants from Bangladesh were arrested
in January 1998, 89 in February , 158 in March, 36 in April and 47
men, women and children were arrested while crossing the border to
India in May. The BDR personnel of the 32nd Battalion recovered
contraband goods worth about Tk. 6 crore during the last five
months of the current year ending on May 31. Goods valued at about
Tk. 5 crore 29 lakh 7 thousand 145 were recovered while entering
into the country. Meanwhile, the BDR personnel recovered goods
worth about Tk 63 lakh 88 thousand 407 while being illegally
transported into India. The BDR filed 45 cases against the owners
of the contraband goods. A total of 693 cases were lodged by them
for the unclaimed goods.
	   The BDR arrested 47 persons in connection with smuggling while
11 absconders were held by them during the last five months. It is
learnt from a source of the 32nd Battalion of BDR at Jhumjhumpur
that contraband goods worth about Tk. 79 lakh 14 thousand 710 were
recovered while entering into the country and goods valued at about
Tk. 1 lakh 40 thousand 939 were recovered while being smuggled into
India in January 1998. Incoming goods worth about Tk. 52 lakh 30
thousand 68 and outgoing goods worth about Tk. 21 lakh 81 thousand
375 were recovered in February. In March, the BDR personnel
recovered incoming Indian goods worth about Tk. 1 crore 92 lakh 6
thousand 120 and outgoing goods valued at Tk. 33 lakh 70 thousand
300.
	   They recovered incoming goods valued at Tk. 1 crore 61 lakh 41
thousand 804 and outgoing goods worth about Tk. 36 thousand 143 in
April. Incoming contraband goods worth about Tk. 44 lakh 14
thousand 443 and outgoing goods valued at Tk. 6 lakh 59 thousand
650 were recovered by the BDR jawans of the 32nd Battalion from
different areas under their jurisdiction in May 1998. The BDR
source said that the recovered goods included various types of
Indian saris, chintz, tortoise shell, sugar, salt, spices, fruits,
three piece, stainless steel utensils, machinery parts, cycle
parts, motor-cycle, transport chassis, toys, suit piece, pant
piece, cosmetics, milk powder, jute seeds, phensidyl, ready-made
garments, imitation ornaments, yarn, pen nibs, pesticides and
cassettes.
	   
</TEXT>
