	   More than 100 feet area of the T-head of Sailabari groyne in
sadar thana has been washed away by strong currents of the river
Jamuna causing loss amounting to Tk. three crore on Sunday night .
It is learnt that the T-head of Sailabari groyen had been
threatened by erosion for the last two years but the local
authorities of the Water Development Board (WDB) did not take any
step to protect the groyen which played a vital role in arresting
erosion at the area.
	   With the sharp rise in the water level of the Jamuna, strong
currents caused by onrush of the northern hilly waters hit the
T-head of the groyen and on Monday night about 100 feet area of the
T-head was washed away creating 50 feet depth at the area. Timely
steps to protect the groyen might have cost hardly Tk 10 to Tk 12
lakh , but due to collapsing the T-head about Tk three crore will
be needed to reconstruct the same. The WDB authorities have started
dumping of cement concrete blocks and boulders at the affected area
with little result due to maximum depth of water in the Jamuna.
	   
</TEXT>
