Dozens end protest outside U.S. Embassy
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) _ More than a dozen members of a
self-proclaimed ``pro reform'' group ended a protest Wednesday in
front of the U.S. Embassy after being persuaded to leave by
security personnel.
	   The demonstrators left in the evening after a five hour protest
to demand Washington speed up a dlrs 43 billion bailout plan by the
International Monetary Fund.
	   ``Where is your promise IMF'' and ``We care about people, not
about politics'' read banners displayed in the peaceful protest.
	   Wednesday's protest was the latest in a series outside the
embassy since last week.
	   Early in the day, Hubert Neiss, top IMF's official in Asia,
arrived in Jakarta to conduct a thorough review of the IMF-led
bailout for Indonesia. 	   
