<HEADLINE>
Germany opposes intervening in Kosovo without U.N. mandate
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BONN, Germany (AP) _ Germany said Tuesday it would not support
any military intervention in Yugoslavia's separatist republic of
Kosovo without a U.N. mandate.
	   In response to a reporter's question, government spokesman Otto
Hauser said that Germany would not support such an intervention
without a U.N. mandate, even in the case of an ``emergency.''
	   NATO defense ministers were to meet in Brussels on Thursday and
Friday to consider military options, expected to include direct
intervention to stop violence between Serbian forces and separatist
ethnic Albanians. More than 250 people have died in clashes in
Kosovo since early March.
