<HEADLINE>
IDT defies slump with 30pc profit rise, HONGKONG STANDARD
</HEADLINE>
IDT defies slump with 30pc profit rise, HONGKONG STANDARD &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   HONG KONG
   ENGLISH
   Margery TamASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE electronics manufacturer and distributor, IDT International,
has escaped adverse effects of the economic crisis, posting a 30
per cent increase in profits amounting to $180.8 million for the
year to 31 March 1998. The turnover of the company was $1.7
billion, a 55 per cent increase from $1.1 billion in the previous
period.
	   Total earnings per share were 19.4 cents comparing with 16.4
cents in the previous financial year.
	   The directors have recommended paying shareholders a final
dividend of 6 cents per share, bringing dividends for the year to
8.5 cents per share.
	   ``The group has not been adversely affected by the recent
financial turmoil and economic downturn in the Asian region since
its manufacturing operations are entirely located on the mainland,
and sales to the Asian markets, excluding Japan, are very small,
while sales to customers in the major markets of Europe, the USA
and Japan, are conducted either in US dollars or the currencies of
those countries,'' said IDT International chairman Raymond Chan.
	   ``I am very happy that the financial year ended 31 March 1998
has been another fruitful year for us and all core business
divisions performed very favourably,'' said Mr Chan.
	   ``The first two months of the new financial year showed a
satisfactory beginning to the year with sales in line with
management plans and ahead of the same period last year,'' he
added.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 HONGKONG STANDARD all rights reserved as
distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
