<HEADLINE>
Giants beat Tigers 6-2, move into first place
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Balvino Galvez pitched a seven-hitter and drove in
two runs as the Yomiuri Giants beat the Hanshin Tigers 6-2
Wednesday and moved into first place in the Central League.
	   Galvez (4-5), formerly with the Texas Rangers, singled home two
runs in a four-run fourth inning at Koshien Stadium.
	   The Giants now have a half game lead over the Hiroshima Toyo
Carp who lost to the Chunichi Dragons 4-3 at Hiroshima.
	   The Dragons' Leo Gomez hit a three-run homerun against the
Carp's starter Nathan Minchey in the seventh inning.
	   Gomez, formerly with the Chicago Cubs, has nine homers. Minchey,
formerly with the Boston Red Sox, slipped to 5-5.
	   A scheduled game between the Yakult Swallows and the Yokohama
BayStars at Tokyo's Jingu Stadium was rained out.
	   In the Pacific League, the front-running Nippon Ham Fighters
blanked the Orix BlueWave 6-0 on three home runs, including a
two-run home run by Jerry Brooks in the first inning.
	   Brooks, formerly with the Florida Marlins, has 12 homers this
season.
	   The BlueWave suffered their fifth straight defeat.
	   The Fighters, who extended their winning streak to three, are 1
1/2 games ahead of the second place Fukuoka Daiei Hawks, whose
scheduled game with the Seibu Lions at Sendai was rained out.
	   Another scheduled game between the Chiba Lotte Marines and the
Kintetsu Buffaloes at Chiba was rained out.
 &UR; (sk)
</TEXT>
