<HEADLINE>
Nokia to expand further in China with new factory
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HELSINKI, Finland (AP) _ Finnish telecommunications group Nokia
will build a new equipment manufacturing plant in the eastern
Chinese province of Jiangsu, Nokia said Wednesday.
	   The new plant will make digital mobile phone base stations and
equipment.
	   The factory, to be situated in Suzhou Industrial Park, will
begin deliveries in 1999 and will initially employ 300 people. It
will be Nokia's seventh production site in China.
	   Nokia views China as one if its most promising mobile phone
markets. Last year, it announced dlrs 750 million of deals to
supply mobile phone networks and equipment there.
