<HEADLINE>
`Driver knocked me down when I refused to move', NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
`Driver knocked me down when I refused to move', NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Tues. - A 32-year-old housewife told the Sessions
Court today that she was knocked down by a motorist driving a
Proton Wira after she refused to move from a vacant parking lot.
	   Koo Mei Fong said the motorist also knocked down her
two-year-old daughter Chiew Yuen Kee and her niece Chin Sim Yee who
were with her.
	   She said she saw Chin, who was pinned under the vehicle, asking
for help and a woman carrying Chiew.
	   Koo said she had earlier been threatened by the driver when she
refused to move away from the empty parking lot.
	   Koo was giving evidence at the trial of businessman Teh Chuan
Ann, 40, who is charged with attempting to commit culpable homicide
not amounting to murder of Koo, Chiew and Chin.
	   Teh, of Taman Tenaga, Cheras, is alleged to have committed the
offence on Jan 25, this year, about 7.30pm at the Jaya Jusco
supermarket car park in Taman Maluri, Cheras.
	   He also claimed trial to two separate charges of committing
mischief by causing damage of above RM25 to the vehicles owned by
Lau Kiat Kean and Liong Mun Kong at the same place and time.
	   Koo said she had told Teh that her sister, May Chan, was going
to park her car at the parking lot.
	   She said Teh replied, ``Try asking your sister to park there and
see what happens.''
	   Koo said at that time she did not believe Teh would drive his
car and knock them down.
	   
</TEXT>
