	   THE State Government aims to get a revenue of RM6 billion from
four million tourists during the Visit Penang Year 1999.
	   State Tourism Committee chairman Datuk Kee Phaik Cheen (BN-Batu
Uban) told the House that the target was realistic based on the
recent tourism revenue and strategies taken by the Visit Penang
Year 1999 organising committee which she chaired.
	   Last year, the State gained about RM4.7 billion revenue from
3.17 million tourists, while in 1996, it was RM5 billion from 3.4
million tourists.
	   Kee said the committee had promoted tourism products and family
reunion, agro-tourism, eco-tourism, heritage trail and shopping
thrill packages.
	   The major events to be held next year are Flora Fest in March,
Penang International Food Festival (April), Penang Golf Circuit
(July and December), Penang Arts Festival (August), Penang Shopping
Carnival (October) and Penang International Trade Fair (November
and December).
	   Kee said a promotional campaign would also be carried out on the
PenangNet homepage.
	   Asked by Tan Cheng Liang (BN-Jawi) on the condition of the
beaches in the State, Kee said the committee was working closely
with the municipalities to ensure that they were clean at all
times.
	   
