	   BAD weather conditions apparently prompted the Paliburg Group to
extend until tomorrow the registration of sales of flats at its
Park Royale residential project in Yuen Long.
	   Registration was originally scheduled to end today while the
first day of sales remains on schedule this Saturday. Last night,
the company said it was offering for sale an extra 50 flats on top
of the 200 units it initially offered.
	   Before last night's announcement, property analysts expected it
to be oversubscribed by about 10 times, as a result of a 10-15 per
cent price discount offered by the company, making the project one
of the cheapest in the New Territories.
	   Midland Realty senior district manager Lawrence Wong Wai-wing
said the subscription rate was an indication of flat prices in Yuen
Long since the project is the first to offer various club
facilities in the district.
	   
