<SLUG> BC-Russia-Tundra Fires </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Tundra on fire in Russian Far East
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Fires are burning in 10,000 hectares (almost
25,000 acres) of tundra in Russia's Far East, the ITAR-Tass news
agency said Wednesday.
	   The moss on the tundra in the Koryak region is dry and easily
catches fire, the news agency said. When the moss absorbs moisture
it serves as the staple food for reindeer in the Koryak region.
	   The region lacks easy access so there was little hope of brining
in firefighters, ITAR-Tass said, quoting the ministry for emergency
situations.
	   (ls) 	   
