<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Klinsmann says no deal yet with Los Angeles
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NICE, France (AP) _ German captain Juergen Klinsmann said
Wednesday he had not made a deal to join the Major League Soccer
team Los Angeles Galaxy after the World Cup.
	   The 33-year-old striker was reacting to a report in the French
newspaper L'Equipe that he had reached a deal with the Galaxy a few
weeks ago.
	   L'Equipe said sources close to Alan Rothenberg, US Soccer chief,
had confirmed the agreement.
	   But Klinsmann denied it. ``It's all made up. there is no deal,''
he said at the German World Cup headquarters near Nice.
	   Klinsmann confirmed, however, that MLS officials had contacted
him in March.
	   ``I made it clear that I would decide only after the World
Cup,'' Klinsmann said.
	   Klinsmann is quitting the national team after the World Cup.
	   After a partly frustrating season, Klinsmann has left his London
club Tottenham and is without a club at the moment.
	   (ns-sl)
