<SLUG> BC-Czech-Airlines </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Government to sell share in airline to foreign bank
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ The Czech government said
Wednesday it is planning to sell a small share in the state-run
Czech Airlines (CSA) to a foreign bank.
	   Transport minister Petr Moos said the state would retain a
majority share in the airline after the possible sale that should
yield at least 500 million koruna (dlrs 15.1 million) into the
company.
	   ``This alternative investor ... is an interim step toward
finding a strategic partner for CSA in the long-run,'' Moos said.
He said the move is aimed at increasing the company's base capital.
	   Talks should be completed before the government steps down
following parliamentary elections scheduled for June 19-20,
according to the minister.
