	   KANGAR, Tues. - Pas has shortlisted four potential candidates
for the Arau parliamentary by-election on July 4, its State
commissioner Hashim Jasin said today.
	   They included Hashim, a medical doctor and a lawyer.
	   Hashim, a college lecturer, said the party's headquarters would
announce the candidate on June 23, a day ahead of nomination day.
	   ``Pas has been active in the constituency due to the looming
general election. When the Arau seat fell vacant following the
death of incumbent Kamaruddin Ahmad of the Barisan Nasional, it was
a matter of us stepping up our activities,'' he added.
	   State BN sources said several names are being considered for the
by- election.
	   Three of these had been submitted to Prime Minister Datuk Seri
Dr Mahathir Mohamad by the Arau Umno division headed by Menteri
Besar Datuk Seri Shahidan Kassim.
	   Topping the list are former Menteri Besar and appointed Umno
supreme council member Tan Sri Dr Abdul Hamid Pawanteh and Senators
Abu Bakar Ismail and Mastika Junaidah Husin, the sources said.
	   The other is Shahidan's political secretary, Baharuddin Ahmad,
they said.
	   
