<SLUG> BC-Norway-Nordic Weapons, 1st Ld Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Nordic weapons makers announce joint venture company
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: Adds comment from Celsius in grafs 3-4. No Pickup &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   OSLO, Norway (AP) _ Three large Nordic defense industry firms
announced plans Wednesday to form an ammunition company.
	   Norway's Raufoss AS, Sweden's Celsius AB and Finland's Patria
Industrier OY said their joint venture would have its headquarters
in Norway and operate under the name Nordisk Amunisjonshus, or the
Nammo group.
	   ``The European defense industry has long been in need of
restructuring and it is natural that this process should start in
the Nordic countries,'' Celsius chief executive office Lars
Josefsson said in a communique.
	   ``United, Nordic defense companies will be much stronger than if
they stand alone,'' he added.
	   Norway is a member of the NATO alliance, while Sweden and
Finland are neutral.
	   The new company, being created from the ammunitions divisions of
all three firms, will have about 1,400 employees and an annual
turnover of roughly 1.5 billion kroner (dlrs 200 million).
	   Raufoss will own a 45 percent stake, while Celsius and Patria
will share the remaining 55 percent.
	   Celsius alone has about 11,000 employees and annual sales of
about 1.5 billion dollars.
	   (dm-ewm)
