<SLUG> BC-Italy-Gucci </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Onetime lover: Gucci ex-wife incapable of having him killed
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MILAN, Italy (AP) _ A businessman who said he had a love affair
with Maurizio Gucci's ex-wife testifed Wednesday that she never
could have arranged the murder of the fashion scion.
	   Patrizia Reggiani Martinelli is on trial for ordering the
killing of Gucci in 1995. Four other people, including the alleged
hit-man, also are defendants.
	   Renato Verona said he had a ``sentimental affair'' with Reggiani
Martinelli in 1994, after the couple divorced, the ANSA news agency
said.
	   Also coming to her defense was a dentist, Andrea Stramezzi, who
said he was a close friend, and corresponds with her now in prison.
	   The two men said Reggiani Martinelli was afraid Gucci would
dissipate the family wealth to the harm of the couple's two
children, ANSA reported.
	   The prosecution says the woman was obsessed with Gucci's estate,
and enraged about an alimony cut, so she allegedly paid her
co-defendants dlrs 300,000 to arrange and carry out his killing.
	   (djw)
</TEXT>
