<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Real Madrid </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Reports: Camacho ready to sign as Real Madrid coach
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MADRID, Spain (AP) _ Former Real Madrid player Jose Antonio
Camacho will be the new coach for his old team and current holder
of the European Champions Cup, news reports said Wednesday.
	   Camacho will sign for the Spanish powerhouse on Thursday, sports
daily Marca reported, although the newspaper did not give details
of the contract.
	   Real Madrid has refused to confirm that Camacho is set to
replace German Jupp Heynckes, who was sacked on May 28th, and
become the team's third coach in three years.
	   ``It is a well known secret but until he (Camacho) actually
signs we cannot confirm it'' club spokeswoman Marta Santesteban
said. ``He would be a popular choice because he is a lifelong
Madrid player.''
	   Camacho, who played for the national Spanish squad 81 times, was
a regular on Real Madrid's first team between 1974 and 1989 when he
retired from the pitch to sit on the bench.
	   He coached first division Espanyol last season.
	   Other reported candidates to take over from Heynckes have been
Sven Goran Eriksson, the Swedish coach of the Italian team Lazio;
Morten Olsen of Ajax; Arsene Wenger of Arsenal; and Ivica Osim of
Strum Graz.
	   (mr/jt)
</TEXT>
