<BODY>
<SLUG> NO-SIGN-OF-LA-NINA sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
No sign of La Nina appearing here, says department, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
No sign of La Nina appearing here, says department, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Tues. - The Meteorological Services Department
today said there was currently no indication that Malaysia will
experience the La Nina phenomenon which brings heavy rains and
probably floods.
	   The department spokesman said should the phenomenon occur, it
might not affect the people as much as the El Nino - the opposite
of La Nina - had for the past few months.
	   ``The effects of La Nina will not be as great as El Nino,'' the
spokesman said when contacted by the New Straits Times.
	   She was responding to a comment by the Singapore Meteorological
Service which claimed that Southeast Asia would be experiencing a
``fairly strong''
	   La Nina, bringing heavy rains and possibly floods.
	   The Malaysian Meteorological Services Department spokesman said
there was not much research done on the La Nina here and most
information was obtained from world meteorological centres.
	   ``Although it is seen as the opposite of El Nino, its effects
are not exactly the opposite,'' she said.
	   She also said indicators at the moment were unclear and that it
was very difficult to conclude the La Nina would occur.
	   Seen as the opposite of the El Nino phenomenon, which results
from the warming of the ocean off the coast of Peru, La Nina is
caused by waters there cooling more than usual, bringing with it
heavier than normal rains.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
