COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   IPOH, Tues - A petrol kiosk operator was punched and robbed of
about RM8,500 by five well-dressed men in Lorong Lahat today.
	   The operator, who only wanted to be known as Fong, said he was
about to open for business about 6.45am when the men drove up in a
Madza 323 car and asked for RM20 worth of petrol.
	   One of them then went to the toilet while the others got out of
the car and stood beside him.
	   After he had filled up the car, one of the men punched Fong
while the other, armed with a knife, forced him into his office.
	   Fong was then ordered to hand over about RM8,000. They also took
a few hundred ringgit from him.
	   
</TEXT>
