<SLUG> OWNER-OF-SHOP-DISTRUBTIN sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Owner of shop distributing porn VCDs arrested, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Owner of shop distributing porn VCDs arrested, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ALOR STAR, Tues. - The Kota Star police believed they had
crippled a group distributing pornographic compact discs following
the arrest of an owner of a video distributing centre yesterday.
	   Kota Star district police chief assistant commissioner Mustafa
Abdullah said a police team from the anti-secret society, gambling
and vice divisions raided a shop at Jalan Sekerat and seized 794
VCDs worth about RM36,000.
	   The team, led by assistant superintendent Wong Chong Fui,
detained the 34-year-old shop owner.
	   Mustafa said the owner would be charged with possessing
pornographic VCDs under Section 292(A) of the Penal Code which
carries a three-year jail sentence or fine or both.
	   
</TEXT>
