<HEADLINE>
Al Fayed to erect tribute to Princess Diana at Harrods department
</HEADLINE>
store

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Mohamed Al Fayed plans to commemorate the first
anniversary of the deaths of Princess Diana and his son, Dodi
Fayed, with a tribute at Harrods department store, his spokesman
said Wednesday.
	   Al Fayed, the multimillionaire owner of Harrods, is considering
erecting an image of the princess and his son encased in the symbol
of a dove, said the spokesman, Laurie Mayer.
	   The tribute may stand outside the store for all passers-by _ not
just Harrod shoppers _ to view, Mayer said.
	   ``It will be permanent,'' he said, adding, ``I think it will be
substantial.''
	   A shrine has been set up beside the store's Egyptian staircase
ever since the couple's Aug. 31 deaths in a Paris car crash.
