<HEADLINE>
Johor Umno convention's sole resolution supports KPRJ, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Johor Umno convention's sole resolution supports KPRJ, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   MERSING, Tues. - The third Johor Umno Convention which ended
today has adopted just one resolution. It gave its full support to
the State infrastructure arm, Kumpulan Prasarana Rakyat Johor.
	   The resolution reads that the convention fully supports the
existence of KPRJ towards fulfilling the demand for justice and
balanced development and State Government's social responsibility
to the people.
	   It was read to the Press by the State Umno liaison secretary
Datuk Mohd Ali Hassan at the end of the convention.
	   Menteri Besar Datuk Abdul Ghani Othman, during a Press
conference later, said that the convention supported the activities
of KPRJ because these were aimed at improving and upgrading
infrastructure in the rural areas.
	   KPRJ, which was established in 1995 to implement projects like
village roads and building and refurbishing mosques and surau, has
come under heavy flak from certain quarters.
	   Some parties have alleged that KPRJ has been competing with
Bumiputera contractors in its undertaking of rural projects, while
others have questioned KPRJ's lack of transparency.
	   
</TEXT>
