<HEADLINE>
Dompok gets pledge of support from Youth, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Dompok gets pledge of support from Youth, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA KINABALU, Tues. - The State Umno youth movement today
expressed full confidence in the leadership of newly-appointed
Chief Minister Tan Sri Bernard Dompok to revitalise the State
economy.
	   Its head Jema Khan Datuk Majid said Dompok's appointment as
Chief Minister under a system to rotate the post among the Muslim
Bumiputera, non-Muslim Bumiputera and Chinese was proof that the
Barisan Nasional was sensitive to the aspirations of the people.
	   Jema, who led a 15-member delegation in a courtesy call on
Dompok at his office at the Sabah Foundation, said Dompok has the
capability and experience to effectively lead the State Government.
	   He said the movement would give its full support to Dompok, who
is also State BN chairman, in dealing with the effects of the
current economic downturn.
	   Earlier, Dompok told a delegation from the Taiwan-based
TransAsia Airways that the State Government would like to see more
airlines flying to Sabah.
	   TransAsia Airways operates flights twice a week from Kaohsiung
to Kota Kinabalu via Taipeh.
	   
