<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Drier air has finally moved over our region today. This drier
air mass will limit the development of clouds and showers over our
area, at least through Friday.
	   However, local weather effects will still cause the development
of clouds and showers over the interior and western sections of
Puerto Rico during the afternoons.
	   Scattered nighttime showers are also possible over the U.S.
Virgin Islands and along the north and east coasts of Puerto Rico.
	   Surface winds continue at or above 20 knots, and this is
creating hazardous conditions across our Atlantic and Caribbean
coastal waters. For this reason, a small craft advisory has been
issued for these waters.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy. A 40 percent chance of showers. Possible
afternoon thunderstorm. Breezy in the afternoon. High 85 to 90.
Wind east at 15 mph, except northeast 15 to 20 mph along the coast.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east with a 30 percent chance of
showers. Fair in the west. Low 75 to 80. Wind east at 5 to 10 mph.
	   Thursday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
High around 90. Wind east at 15 mph.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with 30 percent chance of showers, mostly
this morning. Breezy in the afternoon. High 85 to 90. Wind east at
10 mph, increasing to 15 to 20 mph this afternoon.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind east at 10 mph.
	   Thursday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
High 85 to 90. Wind east at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variable cloudiness with a 40 percent chance of
showers, mainly in the east in the morning and in the west in the
afternoon. Isolated thunderstorms inland. High around 90. Wind
southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the east with a 30 percent chance of
showers. Fair in the west. Low 70 to 80. Wind northeast 5 to 10
mph.
	   Thursday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Isolated thunderstorms. High around 90. Wind southeast 10 to 15
mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny in the morning, becoming mostly cloudy in
the afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east at 10 to 20 mph except for
an afternoon sea breeze less than 10 mph along the coast.
	   Tonight... Decreasing clouds with showers ending, becoming fair
by midnight. Low 65 to 75. Chance of rain is less than 20 percent.
Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   Thursday... Mostly sunny in the morning. Variable cloudiness in
the afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east at 15 mph except for a west
wind less than 10 mph along the west coast in the afternoon.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy in the morning, becoming mostly cloudy in
the afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Possible
thunderstorms. Breezy in the afternoon. High from 75 to 80 in the
mountains to 85 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind east 10 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Becoming partly cloudy in the east with a 30 percent
chance of showers. Fair in the west. Low of 65 to 70 in the
mountains, 70 to 75 in lower valleys. Wind east around 10 mph.
	   Thursday... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variable cloudiness in
the afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms. High from 75 to 80 in the mountains, 85 to 90 in
lower elevations. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of showers mostly
this morning. Breezy afternoon. High around 90. Wind east at 15 to
20 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low around 80. Wind east at 10 mph.
	   Thursday... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
High around 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft advisory due to fresh winds.
	   This afternoon... Wind northeast near 20 kt. Near shore seas 3
to 4 ft. Offshore seas 4 to 6 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east 15 to 20 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4 ft.
Offshore seas 4 to 5 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Thursday... Wind east at 15 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft. Widely scattered
showers.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft advisory due to fresh winds.
	   This afternoon... Wind east near 20 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4
ft. Off shore seas 4 to 6 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east at 15 to 20 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4 ft.
Offshore seas 4 to 5 ft. Scattered showers.
	   Thursday... Wind east at 15 kt. Seas 3 ft. Widely scattered
showers.
