<HEADLINE>
Korda beaten, Krajicek advances at Gerry Weber Open
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HALLE, Germany (AP) _ Top-seeded Petr Korda was beaten in
straight sets Wednesday at the Gerry Weber Open, while No.3 Richard
Krajicek sailed into the quarterfinals behind his big serve.
	   Paul Haarhuis of the Netherlands upset the Czech world No. 3,
7-6 (7-4), 6-4 at the dlrs 875,000 grass tuneup for Wimbledon,
while Krajicek downed German Davis Cup player Tommy Haas, 3-6, 6-4,
6-1.
	   Haas, a 20-year-old German Davis Cup player, twice failed to
break Krajicek's early in the second set, then was worn down by the
Dutch player's powerful serves and greater experience on grass.
	   Krajicek, a 1996 Wimbledon winner who blasted 987 aces last
year, closed out the match in just one hour, 27 minutes.
	   The field has five top 10 players, with French Open champion
Carlos Moya of Spain and defending champion Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia scheduled to play Thursday.
	   Italy's Gianluca Pozzi also beat Australia's Richard Fromberg,
6-1, 7-6 (7-1).
