<HEADLINE>
Air force jets kill 20 civilians, guerrillas say
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW DELHI, India (AP) _ Sri Lankan air force jets bombed targets
in rebel-held territory Wednesday, killing 20 civilians and
wounding about 50, the rebels claimed Wednesday.
	   In a statement faxed to news agencies in India, the rebels said
the jets, supported by artillery, set fire to buildings in the town
of Suthanthirapuram, 250 kilometers (155 miles) northeast of
Colombo, the Sri Lankan capital.
	   Sri Lankan military officials could not be reached for comment
from New Delhi. Sri Lankan journalists were under military
censorship regulations imposed last week. The rebels frequently
accuse the Sri Lankan military of targeting civilians.
	   While there was no way to verfiy the statement, they are
believed to exaggerate casualties.
	   The statement, released from the London office of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam, claimed most of the town was destroyed and
survivors were evacuating the area. 	   
</TEXT>
