<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Italy-Ravanelli, 1st Ld-Writethru,0342 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Italy asks FIFA to replace sick striker
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES thruout with Maldini quotes, player returning to
Italy, Chiesa getting credentials &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SENLIS, France (AP) _ With striker Fabrizio Ravanelli suffering
from an infection in his right lung, Italy on Wednesday obtained
from FIFA a last-minute authorization to replace him on the team
roster with Parma forward Enrico Chiesa.
	   Team officials said Chiesa, 27, got the credentials to become
Italy's 22nd player as the team arrived in Bordeaux to play its
first World Cup match against Chile.
	   The documentation for Ravanelli's substitution was filed by
Italian officials shortly before the expiration of the deadline for
replacing sick or injured players _ the start of the
Brazil-Scotland inaugural World Cup match.
	   Ravanelli, a 29-year-old striker of Olympique Marseille, had
developed a sudden illness after Monday's training. Suffering from
cough and fever he underwent X-ray examinations on Tuesday and was
dropped from the team the next day.
	   ``The fever had reached as high as 40 degrees,'' (104 degrees
Fahrenheit) team doctor Andrea Ferretti said Wednesday.
	   Ferretti added that Ravanelli was responding well to antibiotics
treatment, but will require a rest period of at least a week to
avoid the danger of developing full-blown pneumonia.
	   ``It was a terrible decision to take,'' coach Cesare Maldini
said. ``The medical report left me no other choice. But it cost me
a lot to tell Fabrizio to return home. He understood my decision.''
	   Ravanelli was expected to fly home from Paris Thursday.
	   Chiesa was already in the Italian camp on standby.
	   He had been put on alert as a substitute for forward Alessandro
Del Piero, who has just recovered from a right thigh strain, and
then for Moreno Torricelli, who bruised his foot last week but
resumed practicing Tuesday.
	   Chiesa got a berth on the Italian roster on his third chance.
	   (pv-sl)
</TEXT>
