<HEADLINE>
BAY recapitalisation plan, NATION
</HEADLINE>
BAY recapitalisation plan, NATION &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NATION
   THAILAND
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   BANK of Ayudhya (BAY) is expected to finalise its Bt15-billion
recapitalisation plan Wednesday after which it will make an offer
of new shares to foreign investors, including Brunei's investment
agency.
	   BAY is planning to increase its registered capital from Bt5
billion to Bt20 billion by issuing 1.5 billion new shares at Bt10
par.
	   A senior executive source at BAY said top management of the bank
went to persuade the oil-rich Asean member country to invest in the
bank last weekend. ''There was a conclusion during the talk, but no
details can be disclosed [at this stage],'' he said.
	   BAY will finalise the distribution of 500 million new shares
before deciding to make an offer to the Sultan of Brunei, one of
the world's richest men. If the 500 million shares are not fully
subscribed, the bank plans to offer the remainder to foreign
investors.
	   BAY will also sell 600 million shares, about 30 per cent of the
total 20 billion shares, in private placement to foreign
shareholders and offer another 500 million shares in a rights issue
to local shareholders.
	   BAY closed up Bt0.25 at Bt11.25 per share Tuesday.
	   
</TEXT>
