	   WHILE the Education Ministry does not want students and teachers
to watch World Cup matches live late in the night or early in the
morning, soldiers will be allowed to see the games.
	   Army Commander Chettha Thanajaro said Tuesday soldiers, in
particular conscripts, should be given a chance to watch France '98
which begins Wednesday because the World Cup is ''one of the
wonderful things on earth''.
	   Training programmes will be adjusted so that soldiers have time
to watch late night or early morning matches, he said.
	   ''Soldiers should have a chance to watch the World Cup because
it comes only once in four years,'' he added.
	   
