<HEADLINE>
Carlovers meeting put off, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Carlovers meeting put off, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   CARLOVERS Carwash Ltd, of which the Berjaya Group is a major
shareholder, has postponed a general meeting which was to decide on
a proposed salvage plan after shareholders sought more information
on the company's share valuation. According to Financial Review,
Carlovers had planned to cut debt and fund a restructure of its
operations and new ventures. ``Carlovers has signalled an operating
loss for the full year and in April said it would write down
intangibles and development costs as abnormals totalling A$7
million (RM16.8 million). Its shares have fallen from about A$0.40
last June to 10.5 cents this week,'' the newspaper said. Managing
director Ken Millard is quoted as saying that one or two
shareholders had complained to the Australian Securities Commission
that a report commissioned by the company did not provide
information on a share valuation. Millard said the additional
information would be sent to shareholders today.
	   
