<HEADLINE>
Yugoslav Zoran Njegus signs for Atletico de Madrid
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MADRID, Spain (AP) _ Yugoslav midfielder Zoran Njegus on
Wednesday became the first new player to sign for Atletico de
Madrid since Italian Arrigo Sacchi took over as the Spanish team's
new coach.
	   At a special presentation press conference the 24-year-old
former Red Star Belgrade player said he already knew Atletico's
style because the first division club was very popular in
Yugoslavia.
	   Njegus was born in the same town as the club's ex-coach, Serb
Radomir Antic, who was sacked last month after four seasons at
Atletico and replaced by the Italian Sacchi.
	   The player refused to comment on the irony that it was the new
coach who had brought him to the team.
	   Njegus five-year signing cost about one billion pesetas (dlrs
6.5 million), the national news agency EFE reported.
	   (jt)
