<SLUG> BC-OAU-Guinea-Bissau </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OAU backs Senegalese, Guinean troops in strife-torn Guinea-Bissau
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   OUAGADOUGOU, Burkina Faso (AP) _ The Organization of African
Unity on Wednesday supported the intervention of Senegalese and
Guinean troops to help Guinea-Bissau government troops quash a
rebellion in the West African country.
	   ``All of the facts are not known, but we support any effort to
defend the just, legitimate representative order in that country,''
said the new OAU chairman, Burkina Faso President Blaise Campaore.
``What underpins that initiative is good.''
	   He was speaking to journalists at the end of a three-day summit
of African heads of state in Burkina Faso.
	   ``Bilateral military accords and military assistance between
countries is allowed and normal,'' Campaore said.
	   A Guinea-Bissau parliamentary delegation scheduled a meeting
Wednesday with renegade soldiers holed up in a military
installation since launching a coup attempt four days ago.
	   The rebels had demanded that President Joao Bernardo Vieira and
his government step down and that a transition government be set up
ahead of elections in July.
	   (gam/bk)
