<HEADLINE>
Call to take advantage of Sarawak's resources, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Call to take advantage of Sarawak's resources, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Tan Chin SiangASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUCHING, Sun. - The people should adopt a new mindset to take
advantage of Sarawak's vast reserves of natural resources, Parti
Pesaka Bumiputera Bersatu vice-president Datuk Abang Johari Tun
Abang Openg said.
	   He said one only had to look at the food industry to understand
the situation.
	   Despite having vast tracts of agricultural land, Sarawak, like
other States, imported billions of ringgit worth of food every
year, he said.
	   ``Take, for instance, orchid growing. Singapore, which hardly
has any land left, can still grow orchids for export to Europe.
	   ``If they can do it, why can't we when we have so much land?''
	   Abang Johari, who is also State Industrial Development Minister,
said this when opening the PBB Batu Kawa branch's delegates
conference at Kampung Sebuak Landeh, 27km from here, this morning.
	   Also present were Assistant Housing Minister Dr Abang Abdul Rauf
Abang Zen and Assistant Minister in the Chief Minister's Office
Datuk Sharifah Mordiah Tuanku Fauzi.
	   Abang Johari also said that for the State and country to become
competitive and respected members of the world community, the
people must give top priority to education.
	   On the party, he said members must always put it before self so
that it could serve the people better.
	   ``Leaders like myself, Abang Rauf and Sharifah Mordiah are not
important because we come and go.
	   ``What is important is that the party continues to remain strong
and the direction it is heading is correct.''
	   Abang Johari also stressed the need for party leaders to be
sincere.
	   PBB is the backbone of the State Barisan Nasional and will hold
its triennial general assembly from Aug 27 to 30.
	   The State BN is also made up of the Sarawak United People's
Party, Sarawak National Party and Parti Bansa Dayak Sarawak.
	   
</TEXT>
