	   PENANG, Sun. - Members of the Indian community were today urged
to close ranks and contribute towards speeding up economic
recovery.
	   State MIC chairman Dr K. Rajapathy said the community needed to
be far- sighted.
	   Opening the All Malaysia Malayalee Association's 23rd annual
delegates' conference at Mar Vista Resort, he said: ``While we may
be of different faiths, we should work together.''
	   He said education was a process of which valuable elements in
the Indian culture could be retained.
	   Amma president Dr Joy Varughese, in his speech, urged Malayalees
to preserve their culture, tradition and language.
	   He suggested that Amma work with the Culture, Arts and Tourism
Ministry to promote the Malayalee culture.
	   During a pre-conference dinner yesterday, 69 Malayalees pledged
their organs in the Organ Pledge Campaign. This figure surpassed
the target of 50.
	   The campaign, one of Amma's programmes to help society, kicked
off at the dinner attended by some 150 people.
	   
