<HEADLINE>
Party to form councils if it wins, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Party to form councils if it wins, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 08, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA KINABALU, Sun. - Parti Bersekutu said it will establish
consultative councils for all ministries to evaluate government
policies and programmes if the party forms the next State
Government.
	   The party's acting president, Datuk Harris Mohd Salleh, said in
a statement that this was decided at the party's chief
co-ordinators' meeting held at the Balung River Resort in Tawau,
yesterday.
	   He said the councils would complement the efforts of government
officials by providing input from the private sector, and would be
chaired by the respective ministers.
	   ``These bodies will be similar to those set up by the Federal
Government on ad hoc basis such as groups invited for pre-Budget
dialogue sessions,''
	   Harris added.
	   He said one of the main tasks would be to collate views from the
people, especially from the target groups, to determine the
effectiveness of the policies and programmes, and submit proposals
to the Government on behalf of the private sector.
	   
</TEXT>
