	   UK-BASED Prudential Corporation has completed the acquisition of
an additional 21 per cent stake in Berjaya Prudential Assurance
Bhd, increasing its equity stake to 51 per cent.
	   In a statement issued recently, Prudential Group chief executive
Sir Peter Davis said the move was in line with the group's positive
long-term view of the country and region.
	   Following this, Berjaya Prudential has received approval from
the authorities to change its name to Prudential Assurance Malaysia
Bhd.
	   Berjaya Prudential has been managed by Prudential Corporation
since its inception in 1924.
	   Berjaya Prudential, which has 52 branches nationwide, is the
third largest life insurer in Malaysia.
	   In a separate statement, Berjaya Capital Bhd said its divestment
of the 68.83 per cent stake in Berjaya Prudential for RM722.715
million had been completed.
	   The attributable exceptional gain to Berjaya Capital from this
transaction is RM622.72 million.
	   
</TEXT>
