<HEADLINE>
Team set up to probe officials' wealth, JAKARTA POST
</HEADLINE>
Team set up to probe officials' wealth, JAKARTA POST &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   JAKARTA POST
   INDONESIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Attorney General's Office has formed a team, headed by
Deputy Attorney General for Civil and State Administrative Courts
Soehanjono, to investigate the wealth of current and past
government officials.
	   ``The results (of the investigation) of officials from both the
central and provincial governments will be announced to the
public,'' the office's spokesman, Barman Zahir, said yesterday.
	   He did not elaborate on when the investigation results would be
announced.
	   The offices of the attorney general, the chief public prosecutor
and public prosecutors have already asked the public to provide
information on the wealth of officials through P.O. Box 777 to help
the team in its investigation.
	   ``P.O. Box 777 has been opened and placed at the offices of the
attorney general, the chief public prosecutor and all public
prosecutors in the country,'' Zahir said as quoted by Antara.
	   This is expected to make it easier for the public to present
information or preliminary evidence on the wealth of serving and
former officials.
	   Deputy Attorney General Ismudjoko SH had previously asked all
public prosecutor offices throughout the country to open the post
office box address. The public should use this to provide any
information on the wealth of officials, Zahir said. 
</TEXT>
