<SLUG> OPEN-BURNING sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
69 may face action for open burning, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
69 may face action for open burning, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
   Zubaidah Abu BakarASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   IPOH, Mon. - Sixty-nine open burning cases are currently being
considered for prosecution as part of the Government's nationwide
crackdown.
	   The cases were among the 341 detected from the time the
operation was launched on April 8 until last Saturday.
	   Science, Technology and Environment Minister Datuk Law Hieng
Ding said the Government was coming down hard on those responsible
for land and forest fires as open burning has been identified as a
contributing factor to the haze.
	   ``Several cases have been mentioned in court while others are
still under investigation,'' he said at the closing of the 5th
International Chinwoo Wushu competition last night.
	   Law said Asean member countries were trying to work out plans to
prevent forest fires in view of the dry spell.
	   ``An unofficial two-day meeting of Asean ministers in charge of
the environment would be held in Singapore from June 18 to discuss
forest fires.
	   ``This is because the change in wind direction from
northeasterly to northwesterly is expected to bring a dry spell. We
have to prevent forest fires especially in Sumatra, the Riau
Archaepalego and Kalimantan,'' he said.
	   Law said the ministry was also concerned about rain as a result
of the coming La Nina phenomenon, which could be as damaging as its
opposite, the El Nino.
	   While El Nino is a periodic warming of the waters in the eastern
Pacific Ocean, La Nina is marked by a rapid cooling of the seas in
the same area, a phenomenon which tends to bring heavy rain to
areas hit by drought during the El Nino.
	   
</TEXT>
