	   IPOH, Mon. - Three masked men armed with parangs robbed a couple
of their car and about RM20,000 in cash and valuables at their home
today.
	   Police found the couple bound with a telephone wire at their
house in Kampung Kubang Halban after a tip off.
	   Kuala Kangsar district police chief Superintendent Jalaluddin
Abdul Rahman said the couple were awakened at 3.15 am by the three
men who had entered their house through the front door.
	   One of the men, tied the couple with a telephone wire, while the
other two ransacked the house and took away cash and some jewellery
from a cupboard.
	   Jalaluddin said the men later escaped in a car belonging to the
couple.
	   He urged the public to contact the police at 05-7762222 if they
had any information on the incident.
	   
