	   PENANG, Mon. - More than 100 Japanese expatriates working in
Penang participated in a golf tournament yesterday to raise money
for the Yang di-Pertua Negeri Aid Fund.
	   The Nireji Restaurant Golf tournament held at Kristal Golf Club
in Sungai Bakap managed to raise RM14,655.
