<SLUG> TOYOTA'S-HARRIER-HEADS sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Toyota's Harrier heads for new market, NATION
</HEADLINE>
Toyota's Harrier heads for new market, NATION &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NATION
   THAILAND
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   The Toyota Harrier, which is also known as the Lexus RX 300 in
some markets, marks a new direction where sport utility vehicles
(SUV)'s are heading.
	   According to importer SEC Group Co Ltd, the Harrier, which is
the first Lexus-badged off-roader that competes against rivals like
the Mercedes-Benz M-class, successfully combines the handling of a
passenger car to off-roading capabilities of an SUV.
	   ''It's an off-roader that drives like a passenger car,'' a
company official said.
	   Price has been set at Bt3.1 million, which is reasonable
considering the value of the baht against the yen, and the car
comes with full options similar to those sold in Japan.
	   The Harrier is powered by an electronically-fed 3.0-litre
24-valve four-cam V6 that develops 220 horsepower at 5,800rpm and
31.0 kilogramme-metres of torque at 4,800rpm. Thanks to Toyota's
computer-controlled VVT-i (variable valve timing-intelligent)
system, the smooth-revving powerplant provides exceptional
performance and low emissions. Acceleration from start to 100km/h
is claimed at 8.9 seconds.
	   Transmission is a Super ECT four-speed automatic that comes with
three driving modes (economy, sport, winter) that responds to all
driving conditions. Also included in the transmission system is a
manual shift button behind the steering wheel that allows the
driver to shift manually with hands still on the wheel.
	   A 50-50 full-time four-wheel-drive system is supported by an
electronic traction control and ABS brakes working on four disc
brakes for optimum performance. Independent MacPherson strut
layouts are used in both front and rear suspensions.
	   Passive safety highlights include dual front and side airbags,
seatbelts with pretensioners and belt force limiters, a GOA
uniframe safety structure, a four-link wiper blade and discharged
headlights for optimum visibility.
	   Standard features include automatic climate control, leather
upholstery, wooden veneer, five-door central locking with remote,
electric mirror and windows, sound system with CD player, etc.
	   The rear seats could be easily folded for increased luggage
space with a one-touch operation, while backrest recline and
legroom could also be adjusted.
	   The TV monitor located on top of the centre console displays
information regarding the climate control system, sound system,
etc.
	   The Harrier measures 4,575mm in length, 1,815mm in width and
1,665mm in height. Wheelbase in 2,615mm while front and rear track
are 1,565mm and 1,550mm respectively.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NATION all rights reserved as distributed by
WorldSources, Inc. 	   
