Let the ACA probe, says Koh, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Let the ACA probe, says Koh, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PENANG, Mon. - The Penang Island Municipal Council and the
Penang Development Corporation will co-operate fully with the
Anti-Corruption Agency should it decide to investigate the
allegation of unfair allocation of stalls at the Lebuh Gat Macallum
Market Complex.
	   Chief Minister Tan Sri Dr Koh Tsu Koon said this in a statement
today in response to allegations of impropriety by 10 traders at
the Prangin market.
	   The disgruntled traders charged that the whole procedure, from
the purchase of land from the PDC to the allocation of stalls,
lacked transparency and there was impropriety by ``certain key
people.''
	   Koh, who is also PDC chairman, said he had directed the council
and PDC to make all documents related to the market complex project
available if the ACA requested for them.
	   The council and the PDC had also been asked to give full reports
to Koh regarding the matter.
	   ``Both organisations will prepare Press statements to inform the
public about the background of the project, and the principles and
procedures involved in the resettlement exercise conducted by the
council,'' Koh added.
	   The RM62 million project, privatised to the Prangin Market
Traders Association by the PDC, will provide facilities for the
resettlement of traders from the Prangin market.
	   The Prangin market site will make way for a coastal road
development project and phase five of Komtar.
	   A total of 202 traders at the Prangin market will be relocated
to the complex next year.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
