<SLUG> SABAH-TO-HOLD-FOLK-SONG sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Sabah to hold folk song competition, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Sabah to hold folk song competition, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KOTA KINABALU, Mon. - A State-level folk song singing
competition will be held on June 13 to promote and popularise Malay
folk songs.
	   The competition is organised by the Sabah branch of the Culture
and Arts Department, Education Department, Radio Televisyen
Malaysia, State Culture, Youth and Sports Ministry, Sabah Cultural
Board and Kota Kinabalu Artistes Association.
	   It will be held at Putatan Square in Putatan and will be
officiated by Petagas State Assemblyman and State Communication and
Works Minister Datuk Yahya Hussin.
	   Culture and Arts Department Sabah branch director Chua Tek Luwi
said the programme would help create interest in folk songs among
youths in Sabah.
	   It would also provide an opportunity for the people to
appreciate Malay folk songs.
	   Ten finalists, mostly students, will be competing. Winners will
receive prizes and certificates. The champion will also represent
Sabah in the national competition to be held in Kuala Lumpur from
July 24 to 26.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
