AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Mon. - Malaysian football fans, already on
tenterhooks on the eve of the World Cup, now have a chance to win
football paraphernalia autographed by Manchester United's David
Beckham.
	   The Style in Action Challenge contest was kicked off today by
Brylcreem, which recently signed Beckham as its spokesman for its
new hair styling range of gels, sprays and shampoos.
	   Entry forms will be published in newspapers and magazines, and
contestants will have to answer some questions about international
football players and complete a slogan.
	   The grand prize winner gets Beckham's signed England World Cup
jersey, while the first prize winner will get his autographed
Manchester United jersey.
	   Other signed items up for grabs are two pairs of his football
boots and 10 footballs. Remaining winners stand to win 30 special
edition Beckham footballs, limited edition Beckham caps and Beckham
posters.
	   All entries must be received by July 31.
	   ``This is an opportunity for Malaysian football enthusiasts to
own a true collector's item. It is a wonderful piece of football
history,'' said Owen Ow, president of Sara Lee DE in Malaysia and
Singapore. The company is the owner of the Brylcreem brand.
	   Beckham, who has gained as much recognition for his engagement
to Spice Girl Victoria Adams as for his on-field skills, signed the
two-year endorsement contract two months ago.
	   
