	   WORLD CUP FEVER ... The World Cup fever is catching on in
Penang. In a move to kick up excitement, Sheraton Penang has built
a giant football in front of the hotel along Jalan Larut.
	   Passers-by cannot help but stare at the 3.7-metre ball which
weighs a hefty 550 kilogrammes.
	   It was hotel executive assistant manager James Tay Choon Aun's
idea to promote its programmes for the season - the sale of
merchandise and contests for guests.
	   The ``football'' which costs RM3,000 comprises a wooden frame
covered with PVC.
	   Construction was the effort of hotel chief engineer Mohd Khaliff
Abd Aziz and resident artist Bahrudin Salleh who took pains to
ensure a nice round shape which can withstand wind and rain, and is
aesthetically pleasing.
	   
