	   US-based ArrayComm Inc and Nichimen Corporation of Japan
recently signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Institut
Teknologi Mara in an effort to speed the development of
telecommunications products and services targeted for the Malaysian
market.
	   In a statement issued by ArrayComm its president and CEO Karl
Martersteck, said the MoU would pave the way for joint efforts and
hasten the delivery of enhanced wireless local loop solutions.
	   ArrayComm, a manufacturer of wireless telecommunications
products, is a global leader in smart antenna-based wireless
communications solutions.
	   
