<HEADLINE>
Yusof: Bank Kerjasama not going public, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Yusof: Bank Kerjasama not going public, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   BANK Kerjasama Rakyat Malaysia Berhad has no immediate plans to
go public despite having the potential to do so, its chairman Datuk
Dr Yusof Yaacob said.
	   He said although the current national economic climate had
affected business, the co-operative bank enjoyed strong support
from both its customers and depositors.
	   ``Our performance was good until last year when the country was
hit by regional economic problems but public confidence (remains)
good,'' he said after presenting the bank's business tithes (zakat)
amounting to RM125,325.41 to the Perak Religious Affairs Council.
It was handed to the Sultan of Perak at Istana Iskandariah in Kuala
Kangsar, Perak, yesterday.
	   The Sultan later handed the cheque to the department's director
Mohd Yusop Yahaya on behalf of the council.
	   The tithe was for business transacted by the bank's seven
branches in Perak between 1994 and 1996.
	   The bank will pay a total of RM2.6 million in business tithes
for business transacted by 73 branches nationwide in 1994, 1995 and
1996 to the respective State Religious Affairs Councils this year.
	   So far, it has handed tithes to the Religious Councils of
Perlis, Kedah, Terengganu, Kelantan, Selangor, Federal Territory,
Malacca and Sabah.
	   The chairman said talks that the bank was going public were mere
rumours.
	   The bank, which introduced Islamic banking at the end of 1993,
recorded a pre-tax profit RM106 million in 1996.
	   
</TEXT>
