	   RECENT reports suggesting the likely acquisition of certain
non-performing loans or projects by Pengurusan Danaharta Nasional
Bhd are inaccurate, said chief executive officer and managing
director Azman Yahya.
	   ``Danaharta has only begun preliminary work in reviewing the
non- performing loans situation in general and has yet to evaluate
any specific loan,'' he said. He said before any acquisition could
be made, a number of ``milestones'' have to be achieved including
the appointment of a chairman and board of Danaharta, as well as
changes to the legislative framework affected and determining the
company's funding.
	   ``When operational, Danaharta will typically negotiate to
purchase non- performing loans from financial institutions at a
market value, then seek to maximise recovery value via a work-out
or management of the underlying collateral,'' he added.
	   
