<HEADLINE>
Morocco, Norway tied 1-1 at halftime
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: REWRITES lead to clarify &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MONTPELLIER, France (AP) _ Youssef Chippo headed the ball into
his own goal one minute into injury time, tying Morocco and Norway
1-1 at halftime on Wednesday on the first day of the World Cup.
	   Chippo's error came after goalkeeper Driss Benzekri collided
with Henning Berg as they leapt for Stig Inge Bjornebye's free kick
from the left of the box. The ball went off Bjornebye's shoulder
and straight to Chippo, who missed badly as he tried to clear the
ball wide and instead glanced the ball off in the inside of the
post.
	   In the first-ever meeting between the two countries, Morocco
took the lead in the 38th minute after a splendid move by Deportivo
La Coruna midfielder Moustafa El Hadji.
	   After taking a long pass from Tahar, Hadji sped down the left
side and spun defender Dan Eggen around before blasting home a
right-footed shot just inside the right post.
	   ___ &QC; 
 &UR; Lineups &QC; 
	   Morocco_Driss Benzekri; Abdelilah Saber, Abdelkrim El Hadrioui,
Youssef Rossi, Noureddine Naybet; El Moustafa Hadji, Said Chiba,
Youssef Chippo, Tahar; Abdeljilil Hadda, Salaheddine Bassir.
	   Norway_ Frode Grodas; Henning Berg, Dan Eggen, Ronny Johnsen,
Stig Inge Bjornebye; Havard Flo, Oyvind Leonhardsen, Kjetil Rekdal,
Erik Mykland, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer; Tore Andre Flo.
	   Referee_Pirom Un-Prasert, Thailand.
	   (jw)
