Taiping Con bonds rating cut, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Taiping Con bonds rating cut, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   RATING Agency Malaysia Bhd (RAM) has downgraded the long-term
rating of Taiping Consolidated Bhd's RM138.33 million mortgage bond
issue to B3 from BBB3(s). The rating reflects the company's tight
cashflow position and the uncertainties in its ability to unlock
its asset base in time to redeem the bonds. Furthermore, RAM said,
the suffix (s) was applied in the previous rating as the bond issue
is structured with a first legal charge against the Lot 10 Shopping
Centre which due to the prevailing economic downturn the prospects
of realising its value or raising funds against the building is
seen to be poor. RAM also said Taiping Consolidated is highly
geared with significant amounts of debt taken up to finance its
projects and with the exception of the bond issue, all other debts
are sensitive to the present high interest scenario.
	   
</TEXT>
