<HEADLINE>
Musa proposes measures to help economy recover, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Musa proposes measures to help economy recover, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Mon. - Former Deputy Prime Minister Tan Sri Musa
Hitam today proposed several measures that could be implemented by
the Government to help the economy recover.
	   They included formulating a comprehensive and co-ordinated
package of action programmes; being credible, transparent and
accountable in its moves; and not being involved in bailouts.
	   Speaking at a function organised by the Institution Of Engineers
at Hyatt Regency in Johor Baru today, Musa said: ``Firstly, we have
to offer a much more comprehensive and co-ordinated package of
action programmes for recovery.
	   ``Not in bits and pieces. Not giving different and conflicting
signals.''
	   Secondly, he said, the Government's credibility should always be
evident in its actions.
	   ``If we say that we practise accountability and transparency, we
should not be seen to deny accountability or accept wrongdoing.
	   ``We should not be seen to refuse to divulge the names of those
responsible for huge borrowings, resulting in huge losses
especially if the financial institution is a public one.''
	   
</TEXT>
