Petronas Carigali does it again, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Petronas Carigali does it again, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 09, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   PETRONAS Carigali Sdn Bhd, the exploration and production arm of
Petronas, has won the Royal Society of Prevention of Accidents
(RoSPa) Occupational Safety Gold Award for 1998.
	   In a statement, Petronas said this was the fifth consecutive
year Petronas Carigali has bagged the award from UK-based RoSPa.
	   ``For winning the award five years in a row, Petronas Carigali
received a gold medal in addition to a certificate from RoSPa.''
	   The awards are presented annually in recognition for
achievements in the management of occupational accidents and
ill-health prevention at workplace.
	   
