team &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Two Israeli teen-agers were feared trapped
under the rubble of their high school gym roof after it collpased
Wednesday in the southern city of Beersheva.
	   Police spokeswoman Linda Menuhin said 13 other boys who were in
the Mekif high school gym playing basketball when the roof began
caving in, succeeded in escaping. One boy was lightly injured and
taken to hospital and two others were missing and believed to be
trapped under the debris.
	   Israeli media reports suggested construction on the site may
have destabilized the roof and led to the collapse. Police said
they had not yet determined what caused the collapse.
