	   KLANG, Tues. - Plastic goods worth more than RM30 million went
up in smoke when fire broke out at a factory manufacturing plastic
products in Jalan Haji Abdul Manan, Meru, today.
	   The fire which broke out at 1.30pm also left 600 employees of
Plastic Centre Groups of Companies Sdn Bhd jobless.
	   The factory director, identified only as Tan, said workers who
spotted the fire at the store immediately alerted their colleagues.
	   ``Fortunately no one was injured in the fire which razed three
blocks of the factory building,'' he added.
	   At the time of the incident, only 200 workers were on duty as it
operates on three shifts.
	   About 55 firemen from five Fire and Rescue Department branches
in Shah Alam, Port Klang, Petaling Jaya, north Klang and south
Klang rushed to the scene in six fire engines including a skylift
and took almost an hour to bring the flames under control.
	   Selangor Fire and Rescue Department director Wan Mohd Nor Wan
Ibrahim who led the operation said strong winds and inflammable
materials caused the fire to spread rapidly.
	   
