<HEADLINE>
Four dead, two seriously hurt in crashes, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Four dead, two seriously hurt in crashes, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   KUANTAN, Tues. - Four people were killed and two others
seriously injured in separate road crashes in Mentakab and Kuantan
yesterday.
	   A 37-year-old woman and her two children died while her husband
was seriously injured after their car collided head-on with a lorry
at Km144 Jalan Kuantan-Kuala Lumpur, near Mentakab at 10.45pm.
	   Yap Lee Hong and her children Lee Kok Hoe, 10, and Lee Ko Onn,
five, died instantly while her husband Lee Ah Loy sustained severe
head injuries.
	   Lee, who was driving the car, has been admitted to the Mentakab
Hospital. The lorry driver and attendant were unhurt.
	   State Public Order and Traffic chief Superintendent Mohd Rani
Abdul Rashid said initial investigation showed that the car was
negotiating a bend when it skidded and collided with the lorry.
	   Earlier at 3.30pm, a motorcyclist died and his pillion rider
seriously injured when their machine crashed into a lorry at Km21
Jalan Kuantan.
	   Che Alias Sulaiman, 20, of Balok died on the spot while Amran
Hamid was admitted to Tengku Ampuan Afzan Hospital.
	   
