	   KUALA LUMPUR, Tues. - Former Malayan Banking Berhad audit
division general manager Ahmad Fisal Abdul Rahman was ordered by
the magistrate's court today to enter his defence on June 25 on a
charge of molesting a female bank worker.
	   Magistrate Ahmad Zaidi Zainal said the prosecution had proved a
prima facie case against Ahmad Fisal, now the Mayban Securities Sdn
Bhd credit control and business development general manager.
	   Ahmad Zaidi made the decision after hearing submissions from
Deputy Public Prosecutor Fatnin Yusof and defence counsel K.
Murali.
	   Ahmad Fisal is alleged to have hugged and touched the woman's
breast in his former office on the 47th floor of Menara Maybank,
Jalan Tun Perak about 8.55am last Aug 4.
	   If found guilty, he faces up to 10 years jail, or a fine or
whipping, or any two of these punishments.
	   
