	   THE Dow Jones index of leading industrial stocks was up slightly
on Monday, as bank, pharmaceutical and technology stocks stood
firm.
	   The Dow was up 31.89 points (0.35 per cent) closing at 9,069.59.
About 538 million shares traded hands with 1,670 gainers, 1,301
losers and 535 unchanged.
	   On the bond market the average yield on bellwether 30-year
Treasury bonds was down to 5.787 per cent compared to 5.79 per cent
on Friday, thanks to the dollar's gains against the yen.
	   Bank stocks were up after the announcement of a merger between
Norwest and Wells Fargo, a deal valued at US$34 billion (RM139
billion).
	   High-tech stocks were up as investors looked for bargains amid
Press reports that Texas Instruments was getting ready to sell its
microchip division to Micron Technologies.
	   
