	   POPULAR HANDICRAFT ... These miniature baskets made from rattan
and bamboo, locally known as wakid, are becoming increasingly
popular among local and foreign tourists.
	   Rozie Haibir, 23, of Kampung Likas, can vouch for this as many
tourists stop at her stall at the handicraft market in Kota
Kinabalu to buy them.
	   She said the baskets were made by her aunts in Kota Belud and
Kudat.
	   They are priced between RM15 and RM100, depending on the size.
	   
