	   THE Malaysian rubber prices ended lower yesterday after a quiet
session on lack of demands.
	   At the close, June International RSS One dropped four sen to
278.0 sen per kg while the SMR 20 shed 3.5 sen to 267 sen per kg.
	   ``There is not much activity today as buyers seem to be not in a
hurry to buy,'' a dealer said.
	   He said the buyers may be expecting prices to move lower as the
prices in the region still continued to slide.
	   The Inro daily market indicator prices for June 7 fell to 196.89
Malaysian/Singapore cents from 198.44 cents on June 5.
	   The five-day moving average dropped to 200.22 cents from 201.60
cents previously.
	   
