	   KUCHING, Tues. - A 76-year-old medicine man was charged in the
magistrate's court today with the murder of a three-year-old boy
last month.
	   However, no plea was taken from Brahim Rais who appeared before
magistrate Mahazan Mat Taib in a courtroom packed with villagers,
relatives of the victim, Hazry Damian, and reporters.
	   Mahazan also ordered Brahim to be remanded in police custody for
14 days after Deputy Public Prosecutor Ahmad Zubir said
investigations had not been completed and the post-mortem report
was not ready.
	   Brahim, of Kampung Siol Kandis here, was charged with the murder
of Hazry at Taman Sapura Indah, Batu Kawa, about 8am on May 26.
	   He was arrested at a house not far from the scene of the killing
the following day.
	   Hazry and his mother Ranchin Chuchu, 25, who also sustained
injuries, were found in a drain by a youth who later lodged a
police report.
	   Hazry suffered head injuries suspected to have been caused by a
hard object.
	   The two were believed to have been attacked while they were
taking their bath at a fire hydrant in Taman Sapura.
	   
</TEXT>
