	   TUMPAT, Tues. - The State Government welcomes cultural activists
for discussions to determine the guidelines for dikir barat
performances, Menteri Besar Datuk Nik Abdul Aziz Nik Mat said.
	   He said the State Government had no intention of imposing a
permanent ban on dikir barat and would lift it in due time.
	   ``For the time being, we welcome parties willing to give us
ideas to revive the State's culture and ensure that the
performances do not contain elements contradictory to Islamic
teachings.''
	   Nik Aziz was speaking to reporters after a ground-breaking
ceremony for the construction of a new building for Sekolah
Menengah Ugama (Arab) Tumpat today.
	   There have been requests from some quarters for a meeting with
him to discuss the State Government's decision to suspend dikir
barat performances in Kelantan.
	   The State Government has suspended all dikir barat performances
since last month when some were found to have abused their permits
by including other entertainment unacceptable to Islam.
	   Nik Aziz said the decision was made in the people's interests,
particularly to check moral decay among youths.
	   ``The State Government is not against culture because it is the
tradition and rights of the people. Some aspects of it, however,
are not good for the people.''
	   
</TEXT>
