	   HONG KONG share prices fell 2.3 per cent in half-day trade
yesterday amid concerns over regional currencies and a further
weakening of the Japanese yen against the US dollar, dealers said.
	   The key Hang Seng index lost 195.17 points to close at 8,391.46
