after gaining 0.2 per cent in previous trade.
	   Half-day turnover amounted to HK$3.281 billion, against Monday's
HK$4.548 billion.
	   Trading was suspended in the morning session as heavy rain
storms caused havoc in Hong Kong, with landslips and flooding
reported throughout the territory.
	   
