	   KOTA BARU, Tues. - The State Dikir Barat Association is prepared
to modify its performances to suit the State Government's
guidelines on entertainment in its bid to preserve traditional art
and culture.
	   Its secretary Mohd Rozi Mohd Yazid said he hoped this move would
persuade the State Government to lift the ban on dikir barat
performances.
	   He said the association would set up a monitoring body to ensure
that performances did not contravene the guidelines.
	   ``This body will be empowered to stop a dikir barat performance
if it breaches the rules set by the State Government.
	   ``The show promoters will also be required to submit a letter to
the association declaring that no other forms of entertainment will
be featured in the dikir barat show.''
	   Mohd Rozi said the promoters and performers would be required to
strictly follow the conditions set by the association to provide
clean entertainment to the public.
	   He said the association was confident that it could promote
dikir barat among the younger generations.
	   He said the association would arrange a meeting with State
Culture, Tourism, Youth and Sports Committee chairman Abdullah
Ya'kub to convey its willingness to adhere to the guidelines.
	   Two weeks ago, Menteri Besar Datuk Nik Abdul Aziz Nik Mat
announced the ban on all dikir barat performances.
	   The decision, reached at a State Executive Council meeting, was
on the grounds that certain quarters had violated the conditions in
the permit by featuring other forms of entertainment which are
contradictory to Islamic teachings.
	   
</TEXT>
