	   KLSE Composite Index futures traded on the Kuala Lumpur Options
and Financial Futures Exchange (KLoffe) tracked the positive note
of the cash market to end higher.
	   Spot June ended 15.2 points higher to close at 508.2 with 2,162
lots traded while July futures gained 15.7 points to settle at 502
with 237 changing hands.
	   Open interest for June and July stood at 17,682 lots and 1,903
lots respectively. An analyst said the futures market closed higher
in tandem with the cash market.
	   However, he said despite yesterday's rise in the cash and
futures market, the overall sentiments for both markets remained
cautious following days of weakness.
	   He added the futures market will continue to monitor the cash
market closely today.
	   He foresees the cash market to stay sidelined in the next few
days ahead of any fresh leads.
	   
