	   THE Malaysian rubber prices ended lower yesterday after a quiet
session on lack of demand.
	   At the close, June International RSS One dropped four sen to 278
sen per kg while the SMR 20 shed 3.5 sen to 267 sen per kg.
	   The Inro daily market indicator prices for June 7 fell to 196.89
Malaysian/Singapore cents from 198.44 cents on June 5. The five-day
moving average dropped to 200.22 cents from 201.60 cents
previously.
	   
