<HEADLINE>
Union Paper acquiring four companies, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Union Paper acquiring four companies, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   UNION Paper Holdings Bhd is disposing of its paper products
business and acquiring four companies which are involved in timber
extraction, contracting, cultivation of oil palm and cocoa, and
have road and bridges maintenance contracts.
	   As a result, Union Paper will get a new set of substantial
shareholders since the restructuring exercise will see the issue of
247.32 million new shares at RM1.35 each. This will result in Union
Paper's issued capital eventually rising to RM291.15 million from
RM17.85 million currently.
	   These new substantial shareholders will also make an offer for
the sale of some of the new shares to existing Union Paper
shareholders and new investors.
	   In a statement issued on behalf of the company, Commerce
International Merchant Bankers Bhd said Union Paper proposed to
acquire the entire interests in Tung Hup Enterprises Sdn Bhd,
Tracpower Sdn Bhd and Syarikat Tung Hup Plantations Sdn Bhd.
	   The stake in Tung Hup will be acquired for RM305.41 million,
satisfied via the issue of 226.23 million Union Paper shares, while
the stake in Tracpower for RM22.48 million will be satisfied via
the issue of 16.65 million new shares. For the stake in Syarikat
Tung Hup at RM5.91 million, 4.37 million new shares will be issued.
	   The company also proposed to acquire one share representing a 25
per cent stake in Marceda Corporation Sdn Bhd for RM68,609. It will
be satisfied with the issue of 50,322 new Union Paper shares.
	   Union Paper said the restructuring exercise was undertaken to
rescue the company through the injection of income-generating
assets and the disposal of its existing loss-making paper business.
	   The disposal of Union Paper Industries Sdn Bhd is to Queeline
Sdn Bhd - an existing substantial shareholder of Union Paper - for
RM1. As at March 31 this year, Union Paper Industries has net
liabilities of RM11.68 million.
	   Union Paper also proposed to increase its authorised share
capital to RM500 million comprising 500 million shares of RM1 each
from RM200 million currently.
	   An employees' share option scheme was proposed with the maximum
number of shares available not exceeding 10 per cent of the issued
capital of Union Paper.
	   
</TEXT>
