<HEADLINE>
Aras Murni Corp Bhd, BUSINESS TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Aras Murni Corp Bhd, BUSINESS TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   ARAS Murni Corp Bhd, formerly known as Inchcape Timuran Bhd,
announced a group pre-tax loss of RM121.28 million for the year
ended December 31 1997 compared to a profit of RM924,000 in the
previous year.
	   This was achieved on interest income of RM249.82 million,
compared to just RM53,000 in the previous year.
	   At company level, there was a pre-tax loss of RM8.90 million on
an interest income of RM10.03 million.
	   Directors said the group's performance was adversely affected by
significant losses incurred by wholly-owned subsidiary Kewangan
Bersatu Bhd due to higher provisions for non-performing loans made
by KBB and was also the result of goodwill written off by the
company.
	   
