Receivers, managers appointed for Omega Securities, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Receivers, managers appointed for Omega Securities, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   THE Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange has appointed public accountants
Abdul Jabbar Abdul Majid and Abdul Halim Mohyiddin of KPMG
Corporate Services Sdn Bhd as receivers and managers of Omega
Securities Sdn Bhd.
	   Abdul Jabbar, who is the president of the Malaysian Association
of Certified Public Accountants, and Abdul Halim will manage the
stockbroking firm's business affairs and property.
	   The appointment was made pursuant to Rule 15B(2)(b) of the KLSE
Rules Relating to Member Companies, and after due consultation with
the Securities Commission, the KLSE said in a statement.
	   ``The appointment was to ensure the protection of public
interests including the interests of clients of Omega Securities
following the revocation of its stockbroking licence.''
	   The KLSE added that its team had been on-site since May 4 to
address inquiries from Omega Securities' clients and remisiers.
	   Omega Securities had its stockbroking licence revoked on June 5.
	   
</TEXT>
