	   KOLEJ Aman, will operate from its RM40 million new building at
Bukit Sentosa near Bukit Beruntung next month.
	   Its students, including the July intake, will thus have a
condusive education enviroment with the latest facilities.
	   About 700 new students will begin their diploma and degree
courses in Business Studies, Business Information, Multimedia,
Accounting, Marketing, Computing and Engineering in the new four
blocks.
	   Among the facilities there are a library, and computer and
engineering laboratories.
	   The computer laboratory will have 60 terminals with Internet
access.
	   Kolej Aman chief operating officer Lawrence K.F. Chow is
confident that parents will find the new campus conducive for the
education of their chidlren.
	   The college easily accessible by road and train from Kuala
Lumpur, is in the heart of a new township flanked by commercial and
industrial development zone and forest reserves. Travelling time is
about 35 minutes.
	   To help outstation students, the college has booked houses close
to the campus and shopping area to serve as hostels at a reasonable
rate.
	   Among courses available are Marketting, Business, Information
Technology and Engineering.
	   Chow said for recreation, students through a unique arrangement
can become student members of the Bukit Beruntung Golf and Country
Club.
	   Kolej Aman also offers post-graduate studies. Since its first
link with Oklahoma City University, it has produced 400 MBA
holders.
	   Its students have also won international recognition by winning
awards.
	   Among them is Che Hong Pee who scored top marks in the
Professional Comprehensive Examination I &AMP; II of the Institute of
Chartered Accounts of New Zealand last year.
	   
</TEXT>
