	   STUDENTS obtaining places in Australian universities through the
IDP Australian Education for the July intake will be given
Australian International Student Card.
	   Among others, the card, which can be used in Australia and 33
other countries, offers discounted telephone rates up to 61 per
cent off the public telephone rates, savings on air travel in
Australia with Ansett Australia plus free membership with
Australia's Global Rewards for frequent flyer programme.
	   The IDP is non-governmental and non-profit organisation
representing 250 Australian universities and colleges.
	   IDP Education Australia's Malaysia director Cynthia Celestine
said among services provided by them are banking assistance, visa
application and help in selecting courses and universities.
	   ``IDP as an independent, international organisation playing a
key role in promoting Australian education offers non-bias advice
on the selection of universities, colleges and schools.''
	   It also offers counselling on living in Australia. Other
services include making accommodation arrangements and
pre-departure orientations.
	   Malaysian students will also receive a RM100 cash travel when
they enrol through IDP Australia.
	   Another benefit is the Co-op Bookshop discount card. The co-op
which has 40 bookshops offers 12 per cent discount for cash, cheque
or debit card purchases and 10 per cent discount for those paying
with bankdraft or credit cards.
	   Celestine said for the July intake, those with good track
records may use their forecast A-level results to apply for places.
	   Registration for the July intake is still open. Enquiries can be
made through e-mail address: idpea &LR; pc.jaring.my Students can also
call IDP Australian Education Malaysia at its Kuala Lumpur
headquarters (Tel: 03-2623755) or branch offices at Subang (03-
7365548; Johor Baru (07-3330668); Penang (04-2624539) and Sibu
(084- 320317).
	   
</TEXT>
