<HEADLINE>
Johor Baru autofair records RM3.8m in sales, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
</HEADLINE>
Johor Baru autofair records RM3.8m in sales, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES &QL; 
   June 10, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   MALAYSIA
   ENGLISH
ASIA WorldSources, Inc. 201 PENNSYLVANIA AVENUE, S.E., 2nd Floor

<TEXT>
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20003 Tel: 202-547-4512 Fax: 202-546-4194
COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH, INC.
AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED HEREIN
MAY BE USED IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
	   EON Motor Ria autofair staged another impressive performance
when 120 units of refurbished Motor Ria Protons and used Protons
worth RM3.8 million were sold in Johor Baru last weekend.
	   The autofair drew 18,000 visitors to the Plaza Angsana car park,
EON Motor Ria Sdn Bhd said in a statement.
	   A total of 48 Proton Sagas, 39 Iswaras, 29 Wiras and 14 Perdanas
were sold.
	   The autofair is part of a major roadshow exercise to bring a
good range of refurbished Proton cars from EON Motor Ria, a
wholly-owned subsidiary of Edaran Otomobil Nasional Bhd, to
consumers nationwide who are looking for affordable used cars.
	   It was previously held in Subang Jaya, Selangor; Ampang and
Wangsa Maju in Kuala Lumpur; as well as Ipoh, Perak; Penang; Alor
Setar and Langkawi in Kedah.
	   Overall, the autofair has recorded sales of about RM23.5
million.
	   The next stopover will be at the A Formosa Fort at Jalan
Parameswara in Malacca from Friday till Sunday (10am to 6pm).
	   
