<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT:
	   NEW:
	   _NIGERIA, Resistance to new leader mounts.
	   _ISRAEL-MOUNT OF CONTENTION, Quiet neighborhood latest Jerusalem
political battleground.
	   _YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO, 20,000 march against Serbian rule.
	   _US-SOUTH KOREA, Kim makes case to Congress for easing North
Korea sanctions.
	   _US-DOING BUSINESS IN KOREA, Kim appeals for investment.
	   _FRANCE-WORLD CUP-THE FANS, Fans' reaction differs.
	   _AIR FRANCE-STRIKE, Air France tries to win back customers.
	   _US-DRAGGING DEATH, Death penalty may be sought in alleged
racial killing.
	   _UN-DRUG SUMMIT, How to wage drug campaign?
	   _SINGAPORE ECONOMY, Reaction to record drop.
	   _SWEDEN-MILITARY YEARBOOK, World still dangerous _ SIPRI.
	   _POLAND-GERMANY-YOUTH CENTER, Poles, German meet again in
reconciliation.
	   _BELARUS-SEWER WAR, Diplomatic sewer war mounts.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   LAGOS, Nigeria _ Resistance to Nigeria's new military leader
mounts amid signs that he is too preoccupied with consolidating his
power base to focus on his vague promise to usher in civilian rule.
NIGERIA. Recap expected by 0100 GMT. By Tim Sullivan. AP Photo
LON103.
	   ALSO MOVED: NIGERIA-POLITICAL PRISONERS. Scores of critics and
foes of Nigeria's late strongman remain imprisoned, their fate
uncertain.
	   ZALA AMBASSA, Ethiopia _ Frightened Ethiopians load their
belongings in donkey carts to flee their village, now occupied by
Eritrean forces. A handful stay, saying the invaders have been
kind. ETHIOPIA-OCCUPIED VILLAGE. Expected by 1900 GMT. By Karin
Davies. AP Photos AMS101-102.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _ETHIOPIA-ERITREA _ Renewed fighting in Eritrea-Ethiopia
conflict; U.S. facilitators to return. By Dianna Cahn. AP Photos
MKL101, LON107.
	   _OAU-ETHIOPIA-ERITREA. African leaders approve peace mission. By
Glenn McKenzie. AP Photo. OUA104
	   JERUSALEM _ Terraced with thousands of Jewish graves, dotted
with venerable Christian churches, home to a quiet Arab
neighborhood, the biblical Mount of Olives has become the latest
battleground in the fight for Jerusalem. ISRAEL-MOUNT OF
CONTENTION. Expected by 0100 GMT. By Laura King. AP Photos
JRL101-5.
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ About 20,000 people fill the streets of
Kosovo's capital on the 60th day of protests against the Serb
crackdown on the province's independence-seeking ethnic Albanians.
YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Has moved. By Ismet Hajdari. AP Photos
PR101-107.
	   With:
	   _ALBANIA-CASH FOR KOSOVO _ Ethnic Albanian emigres in Europe and
the United States are mobilizing cash, supplies in the effort to
turn the Kosovo Liberation Army into a new militia. Expected by
0100 GMT. By Brian Murphy.
	   _US-KOSOVO-COHEN. Cohen: NATO to examine Kosovo options quickly.
AP Photos ROM105-107. Recap expected by 0500 GMT.
	   _FRANCE-US-KOSOVO _ Sanctions ineffective, Contact Group
prepares options. Has moved. By Christopher Burns.
	   WASHINGTON _South Korean President Kim Dae-jung makes his case
to Congress for easing U.S. sanctions on North Korea. US-SOUTH
KOREA. Recap expected by 0100 GMT. By Tom Raum. AP Photos
XCAP101-102, WX102.
	   With:
	   _US-DOING BUSINESS IN KOREA _ Kim Dae-jung appeals to U.S.
business leaders to invest in his nation's battered economy. By
Sally Jacobsen. Expected by 0100 GMT. AP Graphic US KOREA TRADE.
	   WASHINGTON _ The United States is enjoying the best combination
of strong growth and low inflation in 50 years, Federal Reserve
Chairman Alan Greenspan says, but the central bank is ready to
raise interest rates to prevent a labor shortage.
US-ECONOMY-GREENSPAN. Recap by 0100 GMT. By Dave Skidmore.
	   SAINT-DENIS, France _ Brazil wins, Scotland loses _ but the
fans' reactions show how the stakes can vary for different
countries at this year's World Cup. FRANCE-WORLD CUP-THE FANS. Has
moved. By Ian Phillips. AP Photos TLV102, RIO105-7, SAO103,
WCSF105.
	   WITH:
	   AIR FRANCE-STRIKE _ Air France begins the tough job of winning
back customers and erasing losses run up from the pay dispute that
lasted until the World Cup's opening day. Recap by 0100 GMT. AP
Photos PAR104,105, 110.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _FRANCE-WORLD CUP-WORLDS APART _ It's hard being shut out and
still hearing the roar of the crowd. By Christopher Burns. AP Photo
PAR109, CAR101.
	   JASPER, Texas _ Prosecutors will probably seek the death penalty
against three white men charged with dragging a black man to the
death. US-DRAGGING DEATH. Has moved. By Michael Graczyk. AP Photos
XJS107, 111-114.
	   UNITED NATIONS _ World leaders wrap up a three-day U.N. drug
summit still divided on a global campaign. UN-DRUG SUMMIT. Recap by
0100 GMT. By Robert H. Reid. AP Photos XUN101-4.
	   SINGAPORE _ Reaction to the lowest drop in 9 1/2 years in the
benchmark stock index and the weakening Singapore currency.
SINGAPORE ECONOMY. By Laurinda Keys. words Expectable by 0700 gmt.
Will be lead with developments.
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden _ The world remains a dangerous place,
according to the authoritative Stockholm International Peace
Research Institute. SWEDEN-MILITARY YEARBOOK. Expected by 0100 GMT.
By Ed McCullough.
	   WARSAW, Poland _ Polish and German leaders meet again for
reconciliation. POLAND-GERMANY-YOUTH CENTER. Expected by 0100 GMT.
By Andrzej Stylinski.
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium _ The European Commission proposes ending a
worldwide export ban slapped on Britain's cattle raisers. EU-MAD
COW. Lead has moved. By Robert Wielaard AP Photo BRU102.
	   MOSCOW _ A Cold War over diplomatic sewage has broken out in
Belarus, the most unapologetically Soviet of former Soviet
republics. BELARUS-SEWER WAR. Expected by 0100 GMT. By Mitchell
Landsberg. AP Photo MIN101.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: NATO defense ministers begin two-day meeting
Thursday in Brussels. Foreign ministers from United States,
Britain, China, Russia, France, Germany, Japan and Italy meet in
London on Friday to discuss nuclear situation in India and
Pakistan.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	   OSLO, Norway _ In ``Sophie's World,'' philosopher Jostein
Gaarder wrote about a girl and a philosophy teacher who discover
they don't exist. Now they're about to star in a movie.
FEA-NORWAY-SOPHIE'S MOVIE. Expected by 0100 GMT. By Doug Mellgren.
 &UR; Science and Technology
	   SAN DIEGO _ The most ambitious mapping of the heavens ever
undertaken is about to start from a remote observatory in New
Mexico, using the most complex camera ever built. The dlrs 77
million project will probe 40 times farther into the universe than
any earlier survey. SCI-US-FIRST LIGHT. To move as wire time
permits. By Paul Recer. AP Photo NY301.
	   BOSTON _ A group of graduate students at the Massachusetts
Institute of Technology are researching ``wearables'': personal
computers small enough to fit into eyeglasses and hip pouches but
powerful enough to access the world's information. SCI-US-BEYOND
HUMANITY. To move as wire time permits. By Chris Allbritton. AP
Photos NY329,330.
	   BOSTON _ Americans with arthritis have seized on
over-the-counter pills as a new way to ease throbbing knees and
hands, even though the opinion of the medical establishment is
skeptical. MED-US-ARTHRITIS CURE? To move as wire time permits. By
Daniel Q. Haney. AP Photos NY303-4
	   YOUR QUERIES: The Associated Press World Service editors in
charge are Ron Kampeas and Bruce Rule. Questions and story requests
to The Associated Press World Service are welcome. Contact your
local AP bureau or the AP International Desk in New York, telephone
(1) 212-621-1650, fax (1) 212-621-5449. 	   
