<SLUG> BC-Venezuela-Extradition,0121 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Supreme Court orders extradition of Peruvian woman accused of
</HEADLINE>
terrorism &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) _ The Supreme Court Wednesday ordered
the extradition of a Peruvian woman accused of participating in
terrorist acts as a member of the Shining Path guerrilla group.
	   The court said Cecilia Rossana Nunez Chipana, alias ``Comrade
Ana,'' should be sent to Peru with the condition that she not be
executed, which is prohibited in Venezuela.
	   Venezuelan police arrested Nunez last February in an apartment
in downtown Caracas. Peruvian authorities claim she belongs to
Shining Path and was involved in a July 1992 car bomb that killed
21 people in a wealthy Lima neighborhood.
</TEXT>
