<HEADLINE>
Lawmakers condemn shelter that forced vagrant women to walk naked
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Thai lawmakers have condemned officials
at a Bangkok homeless shelter who forced vagrant women to march
naked from their living quarters to communal showers, local papers
reported Thursday.
	   Members of the House of Representatives Committee on Justice and
Human Rights called on the Public Welfare Department, which
oversees the shelter, to punish officials responsible, The Nation
newspaper said.
	   Muk Sulaiman, a committee member, said several of the women had
petitioned the lawmakers to be transferred from the Thanyaburi
Rehabilitation Center in northern Bangkok because of the treatment,
according to The Nation. 	   
