<HEADLINE>
Thai Customs officials find heroin smuggled in milk and juice cans
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Thai Customs officials have made their
largest heroin seizure so far this year, finding 20 kilograms (44
pounds) of the drug in 16 milk and fruit juice cans being mailed to
Cameroon, the Bangkok Post reported Thursday.
	   The high-grade heroin, worth an estimated 6.4 million baht (dlrs
150,000), was discovered during an inspection at the Nana Post
office in Bangkok.
	   Customs officials said the heroin was contained in two parcels
dropped off at the post office on Wednesday. Police were
investigating the parcel's registered sender and recipient, the
Post said.
	   Neighboring Myanmar is one of the world's largest producers of
heroin, and Thailand is regarded as a major smuggling and
transshipment point for drugs. 	   
</TEXT>
