<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-BTI Champions,0150 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mayer defeats Fleming at BTI Champions
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   RALEIGH, North Carolina (AP) _ Gene Mayer defeated Peter Fleming
6-3, 6-2 in the first round of the BTI Champions senior tennis
tournament Wednesday at the Raleigh Racquet Club to advance to a
quarterfinal meeting with top-seeded Jimmy Connors.
	   Eddie Dibbs also reached the quarterfinals with a 7-6 (8-6), 6-4
win over Guillermo Vilas.
	   Mayer, who won two French Open doubles titles during his career
on the men's tour, outlasted Fleming at the baseline to earn the
victory.
	   ``I played solid today,'' Mayer said. ``It's hot and muggy here
so it's hard to hit the ball big, but I'm pleased with the way I
played.''
	   Mayer and Connors have met twice on the senior tour, with
Connors winning both times.
	   The BTI Champions is the second event on the 1998-99 Nuveen
Tour.
</TEXT>
